title: deaconess chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast half in a slice of cheese, then a slice of ham.
Place, seam side down, in shallow baking dish.
In bowl, mix soup with sherry; pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain peas.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix. Let refrigerate for at least 2 days to blend flavors.
Drain to serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend flour, sugar and salt.
Add milk and eggs, mixing well. Stir in all remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish. Bake at 325° until firm.
Cracker crumbs may be added on top.

title: spicy ranch-o dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except Bac*Os in container of electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Stir in Bac*Os.
Chill.
Makes 3 cups dip.

title: potato hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger; place in casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain beans and layer on hamburger; cut up potatoes in cubes and place on next; add mushroom soup diluted with water. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix spices with rice.
Cream sugar and eggs.
Add melted butter, milk and raisins.
Bake in greased dish at 350° until brown.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Brown in a small amount of fat.
Add water, mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, mushrooms and onion.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Make a paste of the flour and water; slowly add to the meat mixture, stirring constantly to avoid lumping.
Simmer until gravy is thick and smooth. Stir in sour cream and bring to boiling point over low heat, but do not boil. Serve over rice.

title: tea punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea and let stand 6 minutes.
Then strain.
Add the sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water, pineapple juice and lemon juice and chill.
Serve in a punch bowl with ice.

title: country steak
directions: Cut round steak into very small pieces.
Brown in small amount of salad oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Good over rice or creamed potatoes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Grease baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Spread cornflakes/cracker on top and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and broccoli thoroughly.
Separate into bite size pieces.
Add onions and pimentos.
Toss gently.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing mix, pour over vegetables.
Mix. Cover and chill overnight.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and Wesson oil.
Add eggs, milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Add vanilla, nuts and prunes.
Bake in an ungreased pan at 300° for 1 hour.
Leave in pan.
While hot, pour on icing, without beating the icing.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef in 1/2 inch thick strips.
Coat with flour seasoned with little salt and pepper.
Brown strips in hot shortening (2 tablespoons).
Drain.
Chop tomatoes and add onions and garlic. Add liquid from tomatoes and 2 cups water.
Cover and cook low until beef is tender.
Add green sweet pepper and cook low, for 10 more minutes.
Serve hot with white rice.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Chill and refrigerate. Serve with a variety of fresh fruit chunks. Especially good with cantaloupe and watermelon. Serves 20 to 25.

title: french loaf
directions: Rub skin with melted butter or bacon fat.
Place on square of foil (heavy-duty if to be placed directly on coals).
Puncture several times with fork.
Wrap in foil, place on grill and bake, turning frequently.
Medium-size takes 45 to 60 minutes.

title: white bridal cake
directions: Step 1:
Line bottoms of two heart shaped or round 9-inch pans with waxed paper.
Put shortening in large mixer bowl and beat well.
Sift in the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add 2/3 of the milk and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl and beaters often.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Fill serving bowl 1/2
full with shredded lettuce.
Add in layers: celery, green
peppers,
onion
and peas.
Sprinkle sugar on top of peas.
Add
a
thin layer of mayonnaise.	Next spread cheeses, then bacon.
Cover bowl and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.

title: fruit bars
directions: Empty about 1/2 package of cake mix into bowl.
Add egg, water and oil.
Blend in remaining cake mix, batter will be thick.
Stir in mincemeat and nuts.
Turn batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
It will appear slightly puffed but will flatten.
Then glaze while warm.
Cut into bars when cool.
Yields 4 dozen bars.

title: kielbasa soup
directions: Cook kale in chicken broth.
Slice sausage.
Add to pot, reduce heat and simmer.
Rinse and drain beans, add to pot.
Add macaroni and simmer 8 minutes.
Stir in pepper sauce.

title: chicken livers and rice
directions: Cook onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add to rice.
Roll liver in flour and saute in butter until brown.
Mix all ingredients and put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: blueberry cake muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
With paper liners, line 18 muffin pan cups, or grease well.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Mix thoroughly by hand, ball and roll in cinnamon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: blueberry syrup
directions: Combine blueberries, syrup and orange peel in a small saucepan.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add to blueberry mixture. Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute or until mixture thickens.

title: pecan cheese crispies
directions: Combine cheese and butter in mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed.
Add hot sauce and mustard gradually with flour until well blended.
Stir in cereal.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on top of pecan halves on ungreased baking sheet and flatten with fork, making crisscross design.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: mixed fruit
directions: Note:
Put juice out of cans with fruit.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together by hand, then shape into balls about the size of a quarter. Bake on large cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: baked chicken
directions: In a large 9 x 13-inch baking dish, add chicken, celery and onions (cut into chunks) and can of soup (according to directions on can).
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour or until chicken is done. Delicious served over cooked noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: beef and barley stew
directions: In a large pot brown beef with onion and garlic.
Drain fat and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes until barley is tender.

title: beef and sauerkraut
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off excess oil.
Drain sauerkraut. In casserole dish, put ground beef, sauerkraut and stewed tomatoes.
Mix well.
Put bread crumbs over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rosie's parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a large glass baking pan with generous coating of nonstick cooking spray (Pam).
Dip chicken in melted margarine, then dip in mixture of dried ingredients, including seasonings.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake approximately 20 minutes, turn over once and bake another 20 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.
Quick, easy and great for diets!
Kids love it!

title: homemade banana ice cream
directions: Mix bananas, sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt in blender (or by hand).
Add condensed milk and pour into ice cream freezer. Finish filling to top of ladle (or fill line) with regular milk. Freeze in ice cream freezer with crushed ice and rock salt.

title: lemon milk sherbet
directions: Dissolve sugar in milk; add lemon juice and salt.
Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve over hot water, making sure it is completely dissolved, then stir into the first mixture.
Freeze until slushy and beat until light and fluffy.
Freeze until firm. Whip with a fork before serving.

title: chicken ala king
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Stir in soup until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serve over toast or rice. Serves 4.

title: tender oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer 1 cup raisins and 1 cup water in saucepan over low heat until raisins are plump (20 to 30 minutes).
Drain raisin liquid into measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisin liquid.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add oats, raisins and chopped nuts.
Drop rounded spoonfuls about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate coconut sheet cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 11 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Heat cooker.
Add butter.
Lightly brown onion and garlic. Blend in flour.
Add water gradually.
Add potatoes, celery and salt.
Cook 25 minutes (until potatoes are tender).
Add hot milk just before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except oats and flour.
Stir in oats and flour.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until lightly brown, about 10 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then roll in olive pieces. Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: mrs. hand's salad
directions: Mix jello and pear juice.
Add mashed pears and cream cheese. Set to gel slightly.
Beat Dream Whip; add to jello.
Add some marshmallows if you like.
Put cherries on top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar until very creamy; set aside.
Grease and flour pan.
Put in bottom of pan coconut and nuts (pecans).
Set aside.
Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Pour cream cheese mixture on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350°.
This will make a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Melt margarine on medium heat.
Add sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Press out in bottom of large pie plate or casserole dish. Peel bananas and slice.
Place on pie crust.
Mix sweetened condensed milk with lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip and all other ingredients.
Mix well and pour on top of bananas in pie shell. Chill; cut into squares.

title: crispy oven chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Coat with mixture of salt, pepper, paprika and biscuit mix.
Melt butter and shortening in baking pan.
Place chicken pieces, skin side down, in pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 425°.
Turn skin side up and continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown and tender.

title: hot chicken salad(casserole)
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese in ungreased 2-quart casserole or 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until hot.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook butter and onion in microwave until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Chop or grate cabbage just after a full moon, when points are up, and signs are one of the fruitful signs.
The signs are: Cancer - crab or breast; Scorpio - scorpion and loins; Pisces - fish and feet.
Boil ingredients and let cool.
Pour over cabbage, which has been loosely packed in quart jars.
Seal until ready to use.
Makes 12 quarts of kraut.

title: beef and burgundy
directions: Place all ingredients in large casserole.
Cover very tightly with foil and another cover.
Cook 3 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Lightly butter.
Saute sausage until lightly browned.
Place 6 slices of bread into 3-quart casserole dish, buttered side up.
Spread 1/2 sausage and cheese over bread. Repeat bread, sausage and cheese layers.
Lightly beat together eggs and milk.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Press down until milk comes through.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lazonga
directions: First put some noodels in a pan.
Then put suace on top, then put cream cheese on top.
Put the white cheese, then eat it!

title: pie crust
directions: Place flour in a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with a fork. Add salt, vinegar, egg and water.
Mix well.
Self-rising flour can be used; omit salt.
Makes 4 or 5 pie crusts.

title: emily's easy fudge
directions: Pour into bowl all the ingredients and melt in microwave for approximately 5 minutes. Stir.
Pour into an oblong glass dish and let cool. Cut into squares.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, nuts and margarine.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: maine blueberry cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Add shortening, 1 cup of sugar, egg and milk.
Stir well, then beat. Add blueberries; mix in.
Sprinkle top of cake batter with sugar after pouring into a greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind everything, then mix in sugar and let stand overnight. You can make it a couple days ahead as this stays well in the refrigerator.
Makes a lot.

title: crumb shake for chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put 1/2 mixture in a paper bag. Put 3 or 4 pieces of chicken in bag and shake.
Do same with remaining chicken.
Put in shallow pan; bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sweet, sweet pickles
directions: Add 3 cups sugar each day for 3 days (9 cups total)

title: low-fat marinated veg-bean salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine corn, kidney beans, green beans, onion and green pepper.
For dressing, combine vinegar, sugar, water, olive oil, celery seed, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well and pour over vegetables.
Stir lightly; cover and chill for 4 to 24 hours.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Makes 12 servings. Total fat 3 g (saturated fat less than 5 g and 0 mg cholesterol).

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Use 1/2 stick of butter to grease pan. Put in chicken. Combine all 3 soups, sour cream and poppy seed and pour over chicken. Crush Ritz crackers over that.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with yellow rice.
tags: cream of cream chicken mushroom soup

title: baked trout montbarry
directions: Season the trout with salt and pepper.
Line a well buttered baking dish with the parsley, onion, chives, chervil, mushrooms and tarragon leaves.
Put the fish on top and pour the melted butter over them.
Cover the dish with buttered foil and bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Beat the egg yolks with the brandy.
Remove the foil from the fish; pour the egg and brandy mixture over them, then sprinkle with the bread crumbs, mixed with the Gruyere cheese and a little dusting of paprika.
Return to the oven and bake until the crumbs are golden brown.
Serve in the baking dish.
The classic accompaniments are large broiled onions and thick tomato slices, grilled, with sauteed mushrooms on each slice.
Serves 6.

title: italian fried cheese
directions: Dip cheese cubes in eggs, drench and flour.
Dip in egg again. Roll cubes in bread crumbs and chill for 1 hour.
Place on wax paper.
Fry cheese in oil and drain on paper towel or bread.
Serve immediately.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Place 1/2 of the cubed bread in 9 x 13 pan.
Top with cubed cream cheese and cover with the rest of bread cubes.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour over the bread.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes. Delicious with sugar, syrup and/or fruit.
All ingredients can be substituted; fat free cheese, milk, or egg beaters.
Serves 8.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry tart pie
directions: Mix oleo and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened.
Mix sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese together and stir in nuts.
Pour over crust. Spread cherry pie filling over top. Chill at least 4 hours before cutting into squares. It is very rich. Serves 12.

title: caramel filled chocolate cookies
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and soda.
Beat sugars and butter until fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs. Beat well. Add flour mixture and blend well.
For each cookie, shape 1 tablespoon dough around 1 Rolo candy to form a ball.
Combine nuts and sugar (1 tablespoon). Roll balls in sugar mixture. Bake 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: raynae's bubble bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Mix sugars, pudding, cinnamon and pecans.
Pour over rolls.
Pour butter or margarine over rolls and dry mixture.
Set out overnight to rise. Do not cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until top is browned. Cool 10 minutes and turn out onto platter.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Boil about 5 minutes after boiling starts.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cut into small squares.

title: golden peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour, sugar and beaten egg; cut in butter until crumbly. Stir in peanuts. Reserving 2 cups crumb mixture, press remaining mixture on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: hobo meals
directions: Wash and slice vegetables.
Lay 4 large squares aluminum foil on counter.
Place a hamburger patty on each, then layer on onions, potatoes and carrots; salt and pepper as you go.
Repeat with another patty and layers of veggies.
Wrap foil around stacks.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven; cover with ketchup.
Feeds 4.

title: hash texas style
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown meat with onion and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender. Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and pepper. Heat thoroughly, then put in an ungreased casserole.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: no bake german chocolate cookies
directions: Mix well sugar and cocoa. Add and mix well, milk. Add 1 stick melted margarine. Bring to a hard boil and boil for 2 min., stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add
peanut butter, vanilla and dry oats. Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper or buttered tray.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Mix onion, soup and tomatoes.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan as follows:
chips, chicken, soup mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: goulash(goulash is a great meal.)
directions: Cut beef into cubes and brown in a little water in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to one hour.
In a large skillet, mix the beef, onions, salt, pepper, garlic, bay leaves and water; cook on medium heat.
In a small bowl, melt the butter and stir in flour until well mixed.
Add this to skillet and stir.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Serve with cooked egg noodles or fried potatoes. Serves 6.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly in large container (6 to 8 quarts).
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or mixer until fine crumbs are obtained and shortening is evenly dispersed.
Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator.
Use within 3 months.
Makes about 15 cups of mix.
Use 3 cups of the mix with 2/3 cup water and mix as usual for biscuits.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix and bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: saucy caraway cabbage(microwave)
directions: For sauce, in a 2 quart casserole, stir together milk, cheese, sauce mix, caraway seed and pepper. Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 3 to 4 minutes (5 to 6 minutes in low wattage oven) or until bubbly.

title: mulled cranberry punch
directions: Heat and simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour.
(Remove spices before serving.)

title: linguine with artichokes
directions: In a large foil baking dish, combine artichokes, bread crumbs, oil, parsley, garlic and grated cheese.
Toss together and bake, uncovered, until mixture is golden brown on top (approximately 30 minutes at 350°).

title: chocolate trifle
directions: In a trifle bowl or large bowl with high sides, prepare cake mix per box instructions, but decrease cooking time by 5 minutes. Prepare pudding per instructions, but use 3 cups milk instead of four.
Crush Heath bars into small pieces.
Crumble 1/2 cake.
Lay in bottom of bowl.
Pour 1/2 (1/4 cup) Kahlua over cake.
Pour 1/2 chocolate pudding over cake and Kahlua.
Put 1/2 crushed Heath bars over all.
Crumble rest of cake mix over all.
Pour 1/2 (1/4 cup) Kahlua over cake.

title: peggy's sweet stuff
directions: Drain pineapple.
Use pie filling of your choice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until good and cold.

title: sweet n sour chicken wings
directions: Salt, pepper and flour chicken wings.
Quick fry until lightly brown.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch oblong dish (spray with Pam). Prepare sauce by blending together all ingredients.
Pour sauce over wings.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Turn wings over and cook for 20 to 30 minutes more.
You may uncover wings to thicken sauce.
Serve warm or cooled to room temperature.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand 1 hour and drain.
Mix 1 cup vinegar, 2 cups sugar, 2 tablespoons mustard seed, and 2 tablespoons celery seed.
Boil 1 minute then cool to warm and pour over pickles.
Keeps in refrigerator for weeks.

title: bisquick and broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Bisquick and milk.
Place in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick and milk; place on top of mixture.
Bake at 450° for 27 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: banana cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat. Add bananas and mix thoroughly. Combine oil and vanilla.
Set aside. Mix salt, flour and soda.
Add to mixture alternately with liquid.
Add nuts and drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Cool.
Ice with Banana Icing. Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: party rye sandwiches
directions: Combine cheese, bacon, stuffed olives, onion and mayonnaise. Spread 1 tablespoon on each rye slice. Top with black olive slices. Broil 2 minutes.

title: easy pigs in the oven
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and salt; drain.
Add soup, water, Minute rice, egg and cabbage.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool.
Cut into chunks. Place half in bottom of bowl.
Pour in half the pudding alternating with remaining cake chunks.
Spread pineapple over entire bowl. Spread cherries over pineapple.
Insert knife around edges for color distribution.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Garnish with chopped pecans.

title: cheese topping for vegetables
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan on low heat, then stir in flour. Turn to medium-high heat and stir in milk.
Continue to stir until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese and salt. Stir until cheese melts.
Makes a delicious topping for asparagus.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Fold all ingredients together. Pour into a 8 x 12 inch glass dish.
Refrigerate. Can be made one day ahead of time.

title: strawberry cream cheese salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water to dissolve jello.
Mash cream cheese with fork or put in blender.
Combine all and put in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Refrigerate.

title: bacon spirals
directions: Cut bacon in half crosswise.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and roll bacon in mixture.
Twist bacon slices into spirals and lay on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: reuben roll
directions: Allow bread dough to thaw in refrigerator overnight.
Grease an 11 x 14-inch cookie sheet. Roll out dough onto cookie sheet. Spread Thousand Island dressing down the middle of the dough.
On top of dressing, put 1/2 pastrami, 1/2 corned beef, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 sauerkraut.
Repeat layers.
Cut dough on the outside edges into 7 to 8 strips.
Crisscross strips over middle and pinch. Brush with egg white. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Slice.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef until crumbly.
Drain off fat and place in bottom of a 9x13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Put a layer of chopped onions on top then spread soup over onions.
Cover with cheese and place Tater Tots, side by side, over cheese. Sprinkle garlic powder over Tater Tots.

title: candied bacon
directions: Cut bacon in half.
Shake a few pieces at a time in a bag with brown sugar.
Place bacon on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove with tongs and place on waxed paper.

title: apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to
Grease
muffin cups; set aside. Sift flour, sugar and
spices into bowl; set aside.
Break egg into separate bowl;
beat
lightly with fork.
Add applesauce, milk and shortening.
Add
flour
mixture.
Stir
just
until blended. Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: spinach alexander
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring, until well blended and smooth.
Do not brown. Add reserved spinach liquid, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs. Stir until cheese melts.
Combine with cooked spinach.
Serve immediately or put into a casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Spicy!!

title: best pot roast ever
directions: Season with salt and pepper and brown good in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven with a cover.
Pour in beer and add dill seed.
Let simmer in a 300° oven for approximately 3 hours or until tender. Remove juices and make gravy.

title: holly berry punch
directions: Combine first 4 items; add ginger ale when ready to serve. Keep cold.
Makes 2 3/4 quarts.

title: mexican rice
directions: In saucepan, mix water, butter, seasoning mix and rice.
Stir until seasoning mix is dissolved.
Bring water to a boil.
Cover and let simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Uncover and let stand 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter.
Add turkey, salt, oregano, garlic and sugar.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and water. Simmer 15 minutes.
Place uncooked noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Pour mixture over it. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vanilla extract
directions: Break up vanilla bean and mix with vodka and sugar.
Age one month in a sealed bottle.
Shake often.
To use, strain off amount called for in recipe.

title: healthy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
In medium bowl, combine next 4 ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures. Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper. Drain. Add taco seasoning, Ro-Tel, soup, milk and Worcestershire. Heat evenly. In a separate bowl, combine cheeses. Wrap cheese into tortilla shells and layer into a baking dish. Pour ground beef mixture over tortillas. Top with remaining cheese. Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a preheated 350° oven. Serve with sour cream.

title: southwest soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add peas, corn, kidney beans, stewed tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes with juices.
Bring to boil. Add Velveeta and let cheese melt.
Ready to serve.

title: dumplings(norwegian)
directions: Mix potatoes and eggs with enough flour to hold together large dumplings.
Drop in boiling salted water.
Cook until done, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut up several slices of bacon into small squares.
Add a large onion (diced) and fry until onion is tender. Thoroughly coat dumplings in this mixture and fry lightly until brown.
I use some butter to fry onions in until transparent.
Pour over the dumplings; this is good.
I don't use bacon grease.
Pour that off.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat all ingredients on low for 1 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium for 1 minute; pour into 2 loaf pans (grease bottoms only).
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
(A glass baking pans takes approximately 20 minutes more.)
Makes 2 loaves.

title: holiday pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to
325°.	Butter	bottom	of pan and line with waxed paper;
set
aside.
Cream
butter
until
soft and fluffy. Add
sugar	gradually,
beating thoroughly.
Blend in vanilla and lemon rind.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Toss
cherries
and
nuts
with 1 cup of flour.	Stir remaining
flour
with salt and fold into batter, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing only until smooth.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Bake 1
hour
and 45 minutes.
Cool on wire rack at least 10 minutes before
turning out onto platter.
Cake will keep several weeks if stored in a tightly covered container.

title: cream of wild mushroom soup
directions: To make cornstarch slurry, dilute cornstarch in water.

title: almond bark fudge
directions: Butter square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Melt bark and milk together; add almonds and extract.
Pour into pan.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours.
One square contains 55 calories.

title: french fried chicken
directions: Heat shortening in electric skillet to 350°.
Have enough to come halfway up on chicken.
Roll chicken pieces in flour and pancake flour.
Place in hot shortening or oil.
Salt chicken. Cover and cook until brown.
Turn over and brown other side.
Take out; place on a paper towel to drain excess oil.
Serve hot.
Time for cooking is about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pat in pastry pie crust
directions: Mix.
Pat in pie pan.
Prick pie crust before baking.
Bake in a 350°
oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix together and roll into thin sheets.
Cut into strips.
May be frozen until ready to cook.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Cook the onion in butter until tender.
Combine ham, eggs, cheese, crackers, milk and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until a knife inserted just off center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks; add flour and soda to mixture alternating with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch greased and floured pans at 350° about 20 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cream of tartar to a boil.
Drop 24 crackers into syrup.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour in pie shell.
Put brown sugar, butter and cinnamon on top of mixture.
Put top pie crust on.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Let cool and serve. Tastes like apple pie.

title: jello cottage cheese salad
directions: Stir jello into Cool Whip to dissolve.
Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese.
Chill.

title: seven seas casserole
directions: Combine soup, water, salt, onion and pepper; bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Make three layers in casserole, using Minute rice (right from the box), peas and tuna.
Add remaining soup. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, cutting through mixture with knife after baking 10 minutes.
If desired, garnish with strips of pimiento.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jello cream
directions: Prepare jello and let chill.
Combine butter, shortening, sugar and eggs, mixing well.
Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Layer dish with graham crackers.
Add part of prepared mixture on graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers, followed by another layer of mixture.
Top with a layer of graham crackers. Pour partially jelled jello on top.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Mix together and pour into a large Pyrex dish; chill.

title: butterfly shrimp
directions: Peel, clean and cut shrimp along the back to butterfly.
Dip in flour, then in egg and finally in crumbs, that have been mixed with
the almonds.
Heat 1/2-inch oil in a frying pan and fry shrimp over medium heat until they curl.
Do not overcook. Serves 2 to 3.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Brown meatballs and put in crock-pot.
Add 1 bottle chili sauce and 1 (10 ounce) jar grape jelly.
Cook 5 hours on low.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and salt.
Mix in the water until it forms a ball of dough.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers.
Then slice onions.
Cover with water.
Add salt.
Let soak for 3 hours, then drain.

title: chicken alphabet soup
directions: In a 5-quart kettle or saucepan, heat oil over a medium heat until hot.
Add chicken and cook, stirring often, until chicken turns white.
Remove to a plate.
Add veggies to pot.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender (3 to 5 minutes). Stir in broth, water, alphabets and spices.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat to medium-low.
Return chicken to pot.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until alphabets and carrots are tender.

title: plantation squares
directions: In large mixing bowl blend together cake mix, 1 egg and melted margarine.
Put into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
In small bowl blend well the cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Pour mixture over first layer.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican soup
directions: Pour broth and water together in 3-quart pan.
Add potatoes, onion, celery and tomatoes.
While this is cooking, cook ground beef and drain.
When all is tender, add Velveeta cheese and stir until melted.
Do not boil after adding cheese.
Do not add any salt or pepper as cheese has enough.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Mix beef, onion, tomatoes with liquid, salt, and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole. Layer the potatoes, corn, lima beans and bell pepper on top.
Bake covered at 375° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with the cheese and continue baking, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hostess ham with lemon sauce
directions: Place ham on rack in shallow pan.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Heat in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Turn ham over and continue to heat for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon applesauce muffins
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla. In a small bowl, combine flour and salt.
In a measuring cup, combine applesauce and baking soda.
Alternately stir in flour mixture and applesauce mixture into creamed butter mixture.
Stir in raisins, if desired.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
12 to 15 muffins.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in crock-pot until tender; reserve broth. Combine vegetables, half cup of broth, soups and vegetables.
Chop chicken and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Combine self-rising flour, milk, margarine, pepper and salt.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Process in blender until smooth.
Makes 1 1/4 cups sweetened condensed milk (1 can).

title: country captain chicken
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Remove from bone.
Make sauce of pepper, onion, tomatoes, mushrooms, almonds, raisin, thyme, curry powder and salt to taste.
Add chicken and let simmer on stove or in casserole for 1 hour.
Sauce should be thin.
Serve over hot rice.
Garnish with raisins and slivered almonds.

title: cake brownies
directions: Beat together brown sugar, shortening and egg.
Then mix the vanilla, cocoa, soda and hot water.
Add to the first mixture. Now mix the flour and salt.
Add to mixture.
Then add milk.
(Add nuts if you like or spread nuts on top of the frosting of chocolate powdered sugar.)
Pour into 10 x 15-inch greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp
directions: Cut bacon in half.
Wrap around shrimp and secure with toothpicks.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour teriyaki sauce over shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until the bacon is crisp.

title: karo chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Stir occasionally thereafter to see that it doesn't burn until it reaches 238° (soft-ball stage). Remove from fire and cool. Add vanilla and beat until fudge is thick and surface begins to dull. Pour into pan oiled with butter. Cut into squares.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with the coloring and cocoa and add to mixture.
Add salt and flour with buttermilk and vanilla.
Alternately add soda and vinegar and don't beat hard just blend well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Thoroughly grease 2 baking sheets.
In large bowl, beat sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla until well combined. Stir in oats, flour, salt, soda and cinnamon until well combined. Stir in raisins. Place dough on cookie sheets.
Bake cookies 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
Store in airtight containers.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Mix in large pot.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: eugene's old fashioned cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add egg to vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Cook at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: low-fat oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick spray. Drop by teaspoonful.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: chicken soup(syrian style)
directions: Cover fowl with water and simmer until tender (about 2 to 3 hours).
Remove chicken; add water to broth (amount you wish) for amount you would like to have.
Add carrots, celery, tomato paste and cinnamon.
Cook until rice is tender.
Add pieces of chicken to soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Brown sausage; pour into colander and rinse with hot water for 1 minute.
Drain well.
Place crescent rolls in prepared dish and spread to cover bottom.
Press perforations to seal together. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs and milk together until well blended.
Pour mixture over cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: reese balls
directions: Melt paraffin on low heat; add chocolate bits and melt.
In mixing bowl combine crumbs, powdered sugar, peanut butter and melted oleo.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet that has been lined with wax paper.
Insert toothpick into ball and dip into chocolate.
Place back on wax paper to dry.

title: ice cream fruit punch
directions: Using a very small ice cream scoop, dip half of ice cream into tiny scoops.
Hold in freezer.
In large bowl or kettle, beat remaining ice cream with chilled juices.
Pour into punch bowl. Add chilled sparkling water.
Float small scoops of ice cream over top.
Makes 50 punch cup servings.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Wash asparagus.
Break off woody ends and discard.
Cut stalks in 1/2-inch pieces.
Drop into boiling water.
Add the 1 teaspoon salt and cook until just tender.
Mash the cooked asparagus in its liquid.

title: southern living strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Stir in orange juice, lemon juice, pineapple juice and strawberries.
Pour into large plastic container and freeze.
Remove from freezer 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Add lemon-lime soda.
Stir until slushy.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and mix all other ingredients.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease a large baking sheet with margarine.
Combine sugar and corn syrup in bowl.
Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Stir in peanuts and cook 2 minutes on High.
Stir and cook on High 2 more minutes. Add margarine; stir and cook 50 seconds on High.
Remove from microwave; beat in soda with a wooden spoon.
Pour onto buttered sheet and spread.
Let cand cool, then break with a spoon.

title: mashed potato bake
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes until smooth.
Add softened cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix in salt, pepper and garlic salt. Place in a 9 x 12-inch greased baking dish.
Dot with butter. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread beans on bottom of oblong glass baking dish and microwave until hot.
Spread picante sauce over beans and sprinkle with cheese; microwave until cheese melts.
Sprinkle onions, tomatoes and olives over top.
If desired, put spoons of sour cream dotted over top.
Serve with chips.

title: beef chili without beans
directions: Place cumin seed in a pie pan and toast in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Heat a 6-quart kettle and saute the bacon until clear.
Add the diced meat and brown over high heat along with the onions, garlic and jalapenos.
When the meat is brown and the onion clear, add the remaining ingredients. Crush the tomatoes and add along with the juice.
Simmer for 1 hour and add any additional seasoning.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients 2 or 3 minutes.
Fold in (with beater on fold) mandarin oranges with juice.
Bake in 9x13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into crosswise slices 1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle with garlic salt lightly.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and bake in a tightly covered dish for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
No water required.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef; drain grease.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish:
first put frozen Tater Tots, then one can of soup, spread ground beef and onions, add another layer of soup, sprinkle corn over that and then spread last 2 cans of soup.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs or paprika, if desired.

title: herb bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Open the cans of biscuits and roll in this melted mixture.
Stand biscuits on their sides in loaf pan, forming 2 rows the length of the pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
This is especially handy when you need bread to go with your spaghetti and you forgot to get some at the store!

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add tomatoes; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add taco mix, buttermilk dressing, pinto beans, pinto beans with jalapenos and corn.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes and simmer.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash whole in 2 quarts water on medium heat until tender.
Mix package of stuffing in melted margarine.
Pour 1/2 of stuffing mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour squash (sliced) on top (mixed with remaining ingredients).
Pour remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all together and cook at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: elderberry pie
directions: Combine in a bowl the berries, lemon juice and water.
Add sugar, salt, flour and cinnamon.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and place crust on top.
Bake at 425° for about 35 minutes or until golden brown.
If you have too much filling, bake extra in a small ovenproof dish and use for making fried pies.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put in bowl in layers cucumbers, onion and green pepper and salt each layer.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Drain.
Rinse and drain for 1 hour.
Heat to boiling:
sugar, white vinegar and mustard seed.
Pour over sliced cukes and put in refrigerator in a glass jar (keep a long time).
Must be kept in refrigerator.

title: party salad
directions: Tear lettuce in a large bowl.
Add onion, peas, cheese and eggs.
A few minutes before serving, add ground beef and coleslaw dressing.

title: old fashioned bread pudding(with apple-raisin sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 8 x 9-inch baking dish with vegetable oil.
Lay the slices of bread in the baking dish in 2 rows overlapping them like shingles.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into an ungreased 13 inch x 9 inch pan.
Make three wells in dry mix.
In well #1, put vanilla. In well #2, put vinegar.
In well #3, put oil.
Pour water over mix and stir well with a spoon.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool completely and frost cake with Poor Man's Icing.

title: glazed lemon cake
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil and eggs. Beat on medium speed for 1 minute.
Gradually beat in soda.
Pour in greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in center. Combine confectioners sugar and lemon juice until smooth. Carefully pour over warm cake.
Cool.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all the ingredients and place in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 1 1/2 hours; stir occasionally.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and mix well the eggs, sweet potatoes, vanilla, sugar, milk and butter.
Spread in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, butter, flour and chopped pecans.
Mix and crumble over top of sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese appetizers
directions: Soften oleo
and
add other ingredients.
Roll in small balls and
place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Combine the ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper in a large pot and cook, stirring until beef is partially done. Drain. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for about 40 minutes or until cabbage is done.

title: quick dinner
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together, add to the cooked macaroni, add tomatoes and cook for 1/2 hour on low.
Serve with salad and breadsticks.
(You can add cheese if you like.)
Makes enough for 4 - 6 people.
DELICIOUS.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date balls
directions: Combine one stick of melted butter, box chopped dates and sugar.
Stir over low heat until gooey.
Add nuts, vanilla and rice krispies.
Roll into small balls and roll the balls in powdered sugar.

title: scalloped cabbage with cheese
directions: Cut cabbage up; cook until tender in boiling salt water. Drain.
Melt the butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Add milk.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Place the cabbage in a greased baking dish.
Layer the cabbage and cheese sauce.
Cover with buttered bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bread crumbs are browned.

title: pear pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell and cover with crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour on bottom rack.

title: cherry preserves
directions: Mix 2 cups cherries and 2 cups sugar and bring to a boil. Then add 2 cups sugar and 2 cups cherries.
Boil for 20 minutes. Pack in jars and seal.

title: cake and chocolate sauce
directions: Mix together cake ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Cook sausage and drain well. Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Add water, bouillon cubes, tomatoes, green pepper, oregano, basil and black pepper.
Bring to a full boil.
Add sausage, zucchini, linguine and Parmesan cheese. Cover.
Cook until zucchini is tender.
Stir often.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Wash cucumber and cut in sticks.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 4 to 5 hours.
Drain and pack solidly into 6 pint jars. Mix remaining ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers, filling to 1/2-inch from top.
Seal and process 5 minutes.
For a sweeter pickle, double the amount of sugar.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion until well done; season with salt and pepper.
Add parsley, refried beans, taco seasoning and water. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and cheese.
Mix well.
Fill each flour tortilla with about 1/3 to 1/2 cup of the meat mixture and roll.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour enchilada sauce over the tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
You can sprinkle extra shredded cheese over top the last 5 minutes of baking, if desired.

title: mom's minestrone
directions: In large pot place first 3 ingredients and cook 2 hours; skim fat.
Add all remaining ingredients and cook for 1 hour, medium to simmer, stirring occasionally.
Then cook ditalini (soup pasta) of desired amounts and add to small amounts of soup.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in Corning Ware dish and bake at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: graham cracker recipe
directions: Divide crackers into sections and place on foil.
Boil the sugar and butter for 2 minutes.
Pour over the crackers.
Sprinkle crackers with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Watch carefully to keep from burning.

title: maid of honor cupcakes
directions: Mix the shortening and sugar, then add eggs.
Blend well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder into mixture.
Add vanilla.
Make little balls and place into small cupcake tin which has been greased (or use mini cupcake papers).
Press down with your fingers.
Make an indentation.
Fill with jam mixture of your choosing (1/2 cup jam and 1/2 cup nuts).
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream; garnish with cherries.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix well and make into loaf or rolls after you've kneaded the mixture on a floured board.
Let rise in pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Butter tops.

title: sunshine flapjacks
directions: Add soda to buttermilk.
Add egg, melted butter and cornmeal. Sift remaining ingredients.
Add alternately with regular milk, mixing well.
Beat until lump-free.
Bake on hot, greased griddle. Makes large, thin pancakes.

title: apple salad
directions: Peel and dice the apples.
Beat the egg yolks, lemon juice, salt, white pepper, mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Heat over slow heat until it begins to boil, stirring constantly.
Then add the cream, beat until it is cool.
Pour over apples and mix thoroughly.

title: homemade lasagna
directions: Lay noodles first.
Lay hamburger next, then lay some cheese, then another layer, until all gone.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.
Take out, put rest of cheese on top and put back in oven until melts.
Serve hot.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Mix in large bowl cottage cheese and Jell-O powder.
Add Cool Whip to cottage cheese and Jell-O mixture.
Drain pineapple and add to mixture.
Fold in marshmallows.
Serve soon after preparing.
Cut recipe in half for single family.
May use orange or peach flavor Jell-O.

title: lemon jello mold
directions: Mix jello and let set as per directions on box.
Then add cream cheese and topping and beat for 1 minute.
Then add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put milk, chocolate chips and marshmallows in microwave dish. Put in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Stir real good and put back in for 1 1/2 minutes more.
Take out and add peanut butter.
Beat real good.
Put in buttered dish until it cools. You can add walnuts, if you want to, or coconut.

title: tropical punch
directions: In large punch bowl, mix pineapple juice, lemonade, water and sugar.
Add ginger ale to mixture just before serving.
Garnish with orange slices, cherries and ice ring.
Serves 75.

title: easy chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift
together dry ingredients (flour, sugar and cinnamon). Bring
to rapid boil in saucepan the oleo, salt, cocoa, oil
and water.
Pour boiled mixture over dry mixture and mix well.
Add eggs,
buttermilk,
soda and vanilla; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash for 10 minutes.
Mix ingredients with squash. Top with cracker and melted butter.
Bake at about 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add chicken breasts and cook until done and lightly browned, about 20 minutes.
Remove chicken to a warm serving platter.	Stir flour into drippings in the skillet and cook for 1 minute.
Add the chicken broth and light cream.
Stir and cook until the sauce thickens and bubbles.
Stir in the mustard.
Return the chicken to the skillet, cover and heat for 10 minutes.
Garnish with tomatoes and sprinkle with parsley. Serves 4.

title: mountain cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add the 6 egg whites, beaten stiffly, very last.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use extra creamy Cool Whip and shape into a mountain form with layers of each until top.
Place cherry on top and enjoy.

title: rose water apple pie
directions: Toss apples with sugar, salt, rose water, nutmeg and cornstarch.
Add to pie shell; dot with butter or margarine and cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: best ever chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve cold on crisp lettuce or on croissants or pita bread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute in butter the onion and mushrooms until tender.
Add mushroom liquid to make 1/2 cup.
Add water or milk.
Add soup and rice with cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Pour cheese mixture over broccoli.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers and melted butter, mixed.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook 12 minutes.
Spread between layers and on top of cake.

title: decorator's icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening with electric mixer.
Add vanilla. Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well on medium speed.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often.
When all sugar has been mixed in, icing will appear dry.
Add milk and beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Keep icing covered with a damp cloth until you are ready to use.
For best results, keep icing in bowl in fridge when not in use.

title: jollof rice(liberia)
directions: In a pot with the oil, brown the chicken well (salted and peppered), then fry the onions and one or two hot peppers (optional).
Boil together the chicken, bouillon cubes, tomato paste, onions, vegetables and raw rice (salt according to taste for the rice).
After bringing to a boil, turn down to low heat for about 30 to 40 minutes, covered, stirring occasionally.

title: goulash
directions: In large pot, add tomatoes and crush with hands, mixer, etc. Add ground beef (already browned), onion, chili powder, garlic (chopped) and red pepper; heat over medium heat, then simmer.

title: aunt nye's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and Crisco; blend well and add egg.
Mix well. Add flour, soda, salt and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
If the mixture is too dry, add a little milk before the raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: canine carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, soda and peanuts.
Mix in egg, oil, vanilla, honey and carrots until well combined.
Pour mixture into cake pan and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and cut in small squares, then serve as added treat.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Mix in remaining ingredients except nutmeg.
Pour into greased Pyrex casserole dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Sit casserole dish into a pan of hot water and bake in 325° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, until knife comes out clean.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops on top of the stove.
Mix soup and milk together to make a sauce.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch slices and put them in a baking pan.
Put pork chops on top of the potatoes and pour the soup on top.
You can add more milk if you think you need more liquid to cover the potatoes.
Cover the dish with foil. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes with foil on.
Then take it off and bake without it until potatoes are tender.

title: healthy chicken
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry.
Coat with yogurt.
Mix bread crumbs and Lipton mix.
Coat breasts with crumb mix.
Place in shallow pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and cool.
Put all in Osterizer and cool in refrigerator.

title: citrus sparkler
directions: In chilled large pitcher, stir well mixed undiluted orange juice concentrate, 2 1/2 juice cans cold water, lime juice and rum flavoring.
Add carbonated beverage and lime slices.

title: roast wild goose with fruit stuffing
directions: Sprinkle goose inside and out with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Prick breast and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in apple, apricots, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Spoon stuffing lightly into cavity. Close opening with skewers and string.
Cover breast with salt pork and cheesecloth soaked in melted bacon fat.
Place goose breast side up on rack in roasting pan.
Roast in preheated 225° oven for about 5 to 6 hours or until tender, basting frequently with bacon fat and drippings in pan.
If age of goose is uncertain, pour 1 cup water into pan and cover last hour of cooking.
Remove cheesecloth, skewers and string.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo and add graham cracker crumbs and make crust. Beat eggs, sugar and 1 stick oleo in blender on high for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Slice bananas on top.
Next add pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and cherries.

title: bean and turkey soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 2 hours.

title: venison roast
directions: Coat roast with 1 can of golden mushroom soup.
Add onion and peppers; season.
Roast at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add the mushrooms, 1 can of golden mushroom soup and the wine.
Roast for another 1/2 hour.
Slice and serve with mushrooms and gravy.

title: cream cheese chocolate chip cake
directions: Slice 1 roll cookie dough into 1/4-inch thick slices and layer in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour over cookie layer.
Slice second roll cookie dough and layer on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°; let cool before cutting.

title: zesty dressing
directions: In a pint jar with tight fitting lid, add oil, vinegar, ketchup, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt, sugar, paprika, pepper, celery, salt and garlic.
Cover and shake well. Refrigerate.
Shake thoroughly before each use.
Serve over greens or vegetables.

title: sweet potato chowder
directions: Pure yams, stock and milk in blender.
Heat mixture in large saucepan.
When hot, add remaining ingredients and stir well.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Beat ingredients 4 minutes. Bake in Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: party mix
directions: Cook all ingredients except cereals, pretzels and nuts over low heat.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in shallow pans and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Chop Oreo cookies in blender (save 1 cup of cookies for topping).
Melt butter and mix crushed cookies with butter in medium bowl.
Press firmly onto bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking dish or pan.
Beat cream cheese and sugar, stir in half of Cool Whip; spread over crust.
In a separate bowl, make pudding according to package directions.
Spread pudding over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top of pudding and top with remaining cookie crumbs.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: chili mostaccioli
directions: Combine hamburg, milk, bread, garlic, onion, salt and pepper. Shape into meat balls.
Brown in oleo.
Remove from pan.
Put soup and water in pan.
Return meat balls to pan.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: favorite chicken squares
directions: Blend margarine and cream cheese until smooth.
Add chicken, chives, pimento, salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: jane's gingerbread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add egg.
Sift and mix dry ingredients and spices and add to molasses mixture. Add the sour cream or milk.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch square pan at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onion, pepper and seasoning to taste.
Remove from heat; add rice, cabbage, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Mix well and place in casserole.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over top. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer, until rice is done.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix the ingredients, except the beef, together.
Overlap the beef and then spread the mixture on the beef.
Roll it up and then refrigerate.
Eat with crackers.

title: roast fresh ham
directions: Roast ham with onions, celery, garlic, cloves and wine in a slow oven (325°) for 5 hours or until meat thermometer registers 185°. Baste frequently. Remove ham from pan and pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat. Add flour and stir until smooth. Add bouillon and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Serve sauce with ham. Garnish ham with orange sections. Serves 12.

title: orange salad
directions: In a double boiler, dissolve marshmallows in milk.
Add one package Jell-O, orange or lemon.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese in crushed pineapple, drained.
Add Jell-O and let cool.
Whip one-half pint whipping cream and add to Jell-O.
Refrigerate to congeal.

title: wild western chili soup
directions: In large heavy pan, brown beef and cook onion with garlic until tender.
Stir to separate meat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: pamela's spanish rice
directions: Combine rice, water, margarine and salt together and cover. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for approximately 20 minutes. Rice will be cooked when all the liquid is absorbed. Remove from heat and let set. Cook bacon, onion, and bell pepper until bacon is brown but not crisp, and onion and pepper is tender. Drain bacon grease, then add 2 tablespoons back into it. Put rice into meat mixture. Add chili powder, garlic powder, tomatoes, and soup. Stir all ingredients together in a large pot or skillet and cook on med-low heat until slightly dry and sticky, about 10 - 15 minutes, stirring often with no lid. You may also omit bell peppers if desired and stuff the mixture into steamed bell peppers for stuffed bell peppers.

title: swiss chard saute
directions: Heat oil in skillet over moderate heat.
Saute onion and garlic for 3 to 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Reduce heat to low.
Add Swiss chard, water, salt and pepper; stir well. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally for 5 to 8 minutes or until chard is wilted and tender.

title: poached apple slices
directions: Combine the sugar, water and dash of salt.
Simmer 5 minutes. Meanwhile, core the apples and cut in 1/2-inch slices. Leave bright peel on. Drop into sugar syrup and cook gently until tender. Remove from heat.
Let apple slices cool in syrup to plump. Drain. Use as trim.

title: hamburger-bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer for a few minutes, then place in casserole and bake uncovered about 30 minutes.

title: snowy fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk (stirring frequently) until 234° on a candy thermometer or until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well until it starts to thicken and pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine the coffee, sugar and water.
Simmer for 1 hour. Chill and add the vanilla and vodka.

title: vegetable vehicles
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: elizabeth's easy lemon pie
directions: Crush graham crackers to make 2 cups.
Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, reserving 1 tablespoon.

title: apple yams
directions: Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and apples.
Add candied yams and nuts.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: huckleberry pie
directions: Cook all until thickened.
Pour in a 9-inch pie shell (baked). Top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour and cocoa; mix well.
Add milk and water; mix thoroughly.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and stir until gravy thickens.
Serve over hot buttered biscuits.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in butter; add soups, broth, Ro-Tel tomatoes and chicken.
Mix well.

title: seafood salad
directions: Remove crust
from bread and cube or break into pieces. Mix all
ingredients
and
refrigerate	several hours or overnight.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Preheat broiler. Mix mayo, cheese, onion, pimiento, mustard and hot pepper sauce in small bowl. Place crackers on baking sheet; spoon about 1 teaspoon cheese mixture onto each cracker. Broil 4-inches from heat 1 to 2 minutes, until puffed and lightly browned. Serve immediately.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados well.
Add lemon juice and juice from inside torido pepper.
Mix well; add rest of ingredients and mix again.

title: hawaiian cooler
directions: Place fruit punch in tall glass.
Add pineapple sherbet.
Add lemon-lime beverage; stir.
Serve topped with whipped cream, pineapple chunks and a cherry.

title: cheddar chicken
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Lightly brown chicken breasts in butter; set aside.
Put frozen broccoli into a baking dish (rectangular or round).
Arrange chicken breasts in with the broccoli; set aside. Heat a skillet, then put in grated Cheddar cheese; pour 1/2 cup beer over the cheese in the skillet, stir constantly.
Pour the cheese/beer sauce over the broccoli/chicken.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or microwave (cover with Saran Wrap) 20 minutes on Medium-high.

title: korean chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender and debone.
(Save broth for chicken soup).
Shred cabbage as for cole slaw.
In bowl mix vinegar, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Add this to cabbage and mix well. Let stand one hour.
Slice onion into very thin pieces.
In small bowl mix together vinegar, sugar, salt and lemon juice; mix with onion.
Let stand one hour.
Drain cabbage and onion and remove all moisture with paper towels.
Slice celery diagonally into slivers. In salad bowl, mix together cabbage, onion, celery and chicken pieces; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top and serve.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetarian supper combination
directions: Mix chicken seasoning with water.
Mix all ingredients together in a two-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes, covered, at 350°.

title: tangy pork chops and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sprinkle the loin pork chops with half the salt and pepper.
Brush all over with 2 tablespoons of salad dressing.

title: cheese log
directions: Shape, sprinkle with parsley or cover with walnuts or almonds. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: krab ball
directions: Place frozen krab in food processor with steel blade.
Process until shredded. Do not drain.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir in cream-style corn.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberry sauce and 1 cup boiling water with mixer until smooth. In another bowl, dissolve 2 boxes Jello and 1 cup boiling water and mix well. Add cranberry mixture and pecans to Jello mixture. Put one half of the mixture into bowl or baking dish and set in freezer for 1 hour. Set other one half of mixture in refrigerator to chill slightly. Then spread sour cream over the first half that is very firm and gently pour the last half on top of the sour cream. Set in refrigerator until firm and serve. This is best when let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries (fresh or frozen) in grinder.
Add sugar to cranberries.
Stir and let set 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, stir boiling water into jello to dissolve.
When cooled, add orange juice.
Pour juice into cranberry mixture and add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cheeseburger turnovers
directions: Brown meat and onion, drain.
Add salt.
On well floured board, roll out 2 biscuits to about a 5-inch circle.
Place 3 tablespoons meat on one side of each circle.
Top with cheese and fold over the pastry.
Seal edges with a fork.
Repeat with remaining biscuits. Prick the top with a fork, bake on ungreased baking sheet 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Cut up dates and add to creamed mixture.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add walnuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Let cool a little.
Roll into walnut-sized balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: children's electrolyte solution
directions: Give 2 teaspoons every 2 or 3 minutes, when child has dehydrated from vomiting and diarrhea, after consulting your doctor.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar and Eagle Brand milk; mix well. Pour rest of ingredients in freezer can and fill to freeze line with milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: apricot slush
directions: Steep the tea bags in boiling water.
Add the brandy, cold water, sugar, orange juice and 3 ounces lemonade and freeze.
Stir after 24 hours.

title: rhubarb raspberry jam
directions: Wash and cut rhubarb in uniform pieces.
Add sugar; let set overnight.
Next day, cook slowly until tender, stirring often. Add 1 or 2 packages raspberry Jell-O, depending on how thick you wish it to be.
Put in jars and keep in refrigerator.

title: spinach dip
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Add enough mayonnaise to stick together.
Mold and serve with assorted crackers.

title: baked rice
directions: Butter casserole; pour in all ingredients. Cover and bake about an hour in 400° oven.
Serves 4.

title: hot dog surprise
directions: Saute vegetables until tender in small amount of oil in skillet.
Cut wieners into 1/2-inch rounds; add to skillet and brown.
Add black pepper, onion salt and chili powder to taste. Add stewed tomatoes.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Serve over hot dog buns, rice or with crackers.
Real tasty.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Mix together cucumbers, onions, garlic and pickling salt; let stand overnight.
Drain brine the next morning.
In a large kettle, combine cucumbers with remaining ingredients; bring to a boil, then pack in jars.
Process for 5 minutes in a boiling water bath.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan.
Add (in order) graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chips, milk, then pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to chill really cool.
Cut into squares.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Start by crumbling 1 cake layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Add a layer of each ingredients with Cool Whip on top.
Do this 3 times.

title: tasty beef stew
directions: Melt butter; add onions, garlic and stew meat.
Cook until meat is tender.
Then add carrots, potatoes, bell pepper, celery, beef broth, salt and pepper.
Add enough water to cook.
Cook until the carrots and potatoes are done.
Thicken up sauce with cornstarch to desired thickness.

title: busy day luncheon soup
directions: Brown ground beef; combine in large kettle with remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli-rice bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add Cheez Whiz and other ingredients.
Sprinkle croutons on top, as desired, before baking. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered, then 10 minutes, uncovered. Makes about a 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together well.
Add remaining ingredients, crunching up Butterfinger bars before adding.
Stir well.
Fill to container line with milk.
Stir again and freeze.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut peppers in half.
Remove stem and seeds.
Wash peppers.
Heat 2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Add peppers.
Cook 5 minutes and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Add only 1/2 of the can.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Place in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover meat on top with remaining sauce, about 1 teaspoon apiece. Bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown turkey burger, then mix together with spaghetti sauce, onions, oregano, parsley and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, diced, boiled eggs and spinach.
Boil noodles until they are soft.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Roll, refrigerate, slice and bake.

title: cranberry salad 3
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add cold water, pineapple and juice.
Chill until thickened.
Add cranberry sauce, apples and nuts.
Chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch
pans.
Bake
at
350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Mix all of above ingredients in a heavy, large pan.
Cook until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; beat until cool.
Pour into a greased with oleo 9 x 14-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Sift last 6 ingredients together.
Combine the sugar, shortening and molasses.
Beat until smooth.
Add buttermilk, eggs, spices and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Do not overbeat.
Divide into 10 equal portions.
Pat each into 10-inch pan or whatever size you have.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes. Remove and cool, and then put filling in.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: After baking, carefully add over top. Bake another 15 to 20 minutes until filling is set.

title: peanut butter "play doh"
directions: Mix together with hands.
If necessary, add a bit more powdered milk until dough feels soft and playful.
Make letters, numbers, shapes, etc., then eat and enjoy.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until tender. Cool and peel.
Slice potatoes thinly.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion and cook another minute or so.
Blend in flour, salt, sugar and pepper. Add vinegar and water.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring well.
Pour this mixture over the sliced potatoes.
Add celery seed and parsley. Toss mixture gently and serve warm.
Leftovers are good warmed up in microwave.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Place mixture in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with 1 cup brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour rectangular pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over bottom of pan.
Over low heat, melt butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour in pan over nuts and coconut; on top of this, pour mixture of confectioners sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together; put in ice cream maker.
Fill to rim with milk.
Churn until frozen.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix dressing mix, oil and dill weed well and pour over crackers.
Stir often until dry.
Add Do-Dads or Chex snack mix.

title: meatballs for a party
directions: Mix all together.
Make 1-inch meatballs.
Cook at 350° about 20 minutes.
Serve on toothpicks with any one of these dipping sauces:

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine and bake in an unbaked pie shell for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and keep covered. Put 2 tablespoons to the cup and pour hot water over.
You may double this.
This is also good when you heat large can of apple juice and add spiced tea. Good for parties.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Cook noodles following directions on box.
Cook ground beef and garlic in 10-inch ceramic skillet in microwave oven 6 minutes. Stir every 2 minutes.
Blend in onion soup, water, tomato paste, tomato sauce, salt, sugar, pepper and oregano.
Stir well.
Cook, covered, in microwave oven 10 minutes.
Stir every 3 minutes.

title: sauerbraten meatballs
directions: Combine beef, 1/4 cup gingersnap crumbs, egg, seeds, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Shape into 20 meatballs. In skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add meatballs. Cook until browned (10 minutes). Remove from pan.

title: mama stafford's egg custard
directions: Mix and pour into unlined pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes one
big or two little pies.
I sprinkle top with nutmeg.

title: ann's cheesey cheese and macaroni(serves 5 to 6)
directions: Wash rice and drain.
Heat oil in a heavy kettle or Dutch oven and brown ham over moderate heat.
Add bell pepper, onions, garlic and chili pepper.
Saute for about 3 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Stir in the squid and add olives.
Stir in the rice and add water to cover contents in kettle by 1/4 to 1/2-inch. Season with salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly and simmer on low heat until liquid is absorbed (about 20 minutes). If dried rice is preferred, uncover and simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: whiskey sours
directions: Add 1 tray of ice cubes, small amounts at a time.
Blend in the blender 10 seconds.

title: night-before french toast
directions: Put bread in a well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients, except butter, and pour over bread in pan.
Cover with foil; refrigerate for 4 to 36 hours.
Uncover, dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until puffy and lightly browned.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.
Serve with powdered sugar or syrup.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Add olive oil, thyme, basil, salt and pepper.
Saute until onion is wilted.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook 10 minutes.
Blend flour with about 5 tablespoons of broth.
Stir into tomato mixture.
Add remaining broth and cook 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add sugar and cream.
Heat until serving temperature.
Serves 8 people.

title: snack time
directions: Serve with juice (summer) or with hot chocolate (winter).

title: peach salad
directions: Boil pineapple for 5 minutes.
Add Jell-O and stir well.
Add buttermilk, then Cool Whip and mix together.
Put in refrigerator and let chill.
Other fruits and flavors may be used.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place popcorn in a 4-inch deep buttered baking pan.
Keep in oven.
In large saucepan, melt butter on low heat.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil and stir constantly.
Now, boil without stirring for 5 minutes. Remove from heat quickly and stir in baking soda and vanilla. Slowly pour syrup mixture over popcorn.
Butter pan for popcorn and mix.
Add nuts before baking.
Bake 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place hen in large pot and add water to 2 or 3-inches above it. Cook until tender, adding water if necessary. Remove chicken from broth when tender.
