Mix flour and egg with enough broth to make a medium dough. Knead until stiff enough to roll. Roll with rolling pin and let stand for 5 minutes. Cut dough into thin squares and drop into boiling chicken broth. Simmer for 10 minutes and let stand in covered pot for 10 more minutes. Serve piping hot with chicken.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Absolutely delicious!
Everyone loves these rich, crisp cookies.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn bread mix and corn.
If too thick, add a little milk. Add cheese and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in greased pan.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Mix all together, then mix with mixer for three minutes.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
If your oven cooks fast, bake at 325°.

title: bran rolls
directions: Mix yeast, lukewarm water and all-bran cereal.
Put together in glass bowl.
Let stand until yeast comes to top (about 15 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand until double in bulk.
Punch down; turn out on floured board.
Shape into small balls.
Place 2 or 3 balls together to form each roll.
Place in a greased muffin pan.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Brush tops with butter.
Cool on rack.
May be frozen in freezer bag for later use.

title: pizza pete's pizza dough
directions: Mix ingredients and add in flour until sticky to touch.
Let rise in warm place.
Grease pans.
Pour dough in pans and pat down with olive oil.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef, which has been cut into strips while frozen, in oil.
Remove and saute onion and pepper which have been cut into large pieces until soft.
Add tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Stir in soy sauce, beef broth and water.
Return beef strips and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir cornstarch into tomato liquid to make a smooth paste, then stir into bubbling beef mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Spoon over spaghetti, potatoes or rice.

title: shrimp and cheese grits
directions: In a large frying pan, cook bacon until crisp. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. Add the onions, bell pepper, oregano and 1-1/2 teaspoons of the salt to pan. Cover and cook over moderate heat, stir occasionally until soft. Uncover and cook until golden. Add tomatoes and paste and cook, stirring until dry, about 4 minutes. Add wine and cook until almost evaporated, then add shrimp and cook, stirring just until done. Stir in 1/2 cup water, the cream, Tabasco and remove from heat.

title: candy kiss cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening and peanut butter together.
Add baking soda and mix.
Mix in milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Mix and shape into balls.
Roll balls in additional sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Top each hot cookie with candy kiss, pressing down into cookie.

title: chicken curry
directions: Indian spices are available in any Asian or Indian stores.

title: lomi salmon
directions: Remove any bones or skin.
Finely chop or shred the salted salmon.
Place in a colander and rinse under cold tap water for approximately 10 minutes or until most of the salt is removed. Allow the salted salmon to drain.

title: spicy ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in oil, add onions.
Cook until tender.
Stir in salt, pepper, oregano, garlic salt, tomatoes, and rice.
Simmer at least 5 minutes (until rice is cooked) stirring occasionally. Place mixture in casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese. Bake at 350° just until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.
If making this ahead, don't put on the cheese until ready to heat to serve.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Slice banana into pie shell.
Prepare pie filling mix as directed on box, using 2 1/2 cups milk.
Fold in 1/2 cup of Cool Whip and pour over banana in shell.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Top with remaining Cool Whip; garnish with banana slices and mint, if desired.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, flour, baking powder, milk, egg, salt and vanilla.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place sliced apples on top of mixture.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon on top.
Add butter on top also.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: one pot quick spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef in Dutch oven.
Stir in onion, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce.
Add salt, sugar, water and uncooked spaghetti.
Heat uncovered to boiling over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 15 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Remove from heat; stir and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: louise's homemade ice cream
directions: Beat
first
3 ingredients together well.
Scald milks. Add egg mixture.
Cook in double boiler (stirring often) until mixture thickens.	Pour into plastic container and completely chill in refrigerator until ready for ice cream freezer.

title: strawberry mousse* * * * *
directions: Dallas is the source of this recipe.
You might know it came from Texas, but it was given to me by a gal from New Jersey.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter or margarine, sugar, brown sugar and egg; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Separately mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to sugar mixture; beat well. Add peanut butter and milk.
Use teaspoon to scoop dough into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and slightly flatten dough with hand.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: seafood file gumbo
directions: You may want to double up on the shrimp and omit the oysters, or you may omit the oysters and substitute scallops. Peel shrimp and reserve heads and tails to make seafood stock. Simmer, uncovered, in 6 cups of water for 1 1/2 hours to make stock. Set aside.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Heat 1 minute; stir-fry chicken in 2 batches until browned.
Remove skillet from heat; spray skillet with cooking spray.
Stir-fry vegetables until crisp.
Add soup, water, soy sauce and ginger; heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat through.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: italian eggplant bake
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling salted water for 3 minutes; drain and place in shallow baking dish.
Cook onions, green pepper, garlic and oregano in butter until tender.
Add soup, water and salt. Heat; pour sauce over eggplant.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes; stir often.
Remove eggplant from oven.
Turn temperature up to 425°.
Top eggplant with croutons; sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a saucepan.
Cook on medium until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat and cool 1 minute.
Add salt, vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: venison bologna
directions: Combine all ingredients as listed.
Mix well.
Grind again. Mix well.
Place in a nonmetallic container and dry for 4 to 5 days in a cool place.
Grind again and stuff in bags or casing. Bake in 200° oven for 3 hours.
Put out to cool.
It is then ready to eat or freeze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Separate chicken and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soups and sour cream and pour on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Crush crackers and mix with butter.
Spread cracker mixture over casserole and cook for 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls about the size of a big marble.
Bake at 350°.
Place balls on cookie sheet for about 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli chinese style
directions: Wash broccoli; cut flowerets off stem.
Peel off stringy outsides and cut stems diagonally in 1-inch pieces.
Parboil broccoli in boiling water which has 1 teaspoon baking soda added to it.
This will help retain the green color of the broccoli. Rinse in cold water and drain.
Heat the oil in a skillet.
Add the broccoli; saute until covered with oil.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover skillet; turn heat down and cook until broccoli is tender, approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix thawed broccoli, onion and eggs together.
Add Jiffy mix and cottage or cream cheese.
Stir until mixed well.
Add melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: recipe for mother
directions: Sift love, patience and work.
Stir in understanding.
Add helpfulness and encouragement.
Blend in scolding and punishment. Add hugs and kisses.
Put in a home with children.
Leave for a lifetime.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain and arrange bread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Place sausage on top, then put cheese on top of sausage.
Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups milk and add mushrooms and mustard.
Pour over sausage and eggs and refrigerate all night.
Next morning, dilute mushroom soup with milk; pour over top and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Hot sausage can be used.)

title: surprise rolls
directions: Mix mayonnaise, salt, celery salt, then add rest.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Stuff mixture into hoagie rolls or hot dog buns.
Brush tops with melted butter and put into oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese starts melting.
Makes approximately 8 rolls.

title: fruit punch
directions: In large punch bowl mix all ingredients well.
Add ice ring if desired.
Serves 28 (1/2 cup each).

title: hot chili spread(appetizer)
directions: Drain chopped chilies thoroughly.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and spread chilies evenly on the bottom.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the chilies.
Mix together the eggs and milk.
Pour over top.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until mixture appears solid.
Spread with a knife on Ritz crackers.

title: colored macaroni
directions: Mix alcohol and food coloring.
Stir in macaroni.
Spread on cookie sheets to dry.
String on shoelace to make necklaces or glue on paper to make pictures.

title: brownie cool split
directions: In a large bowl, layer broken brownies, Cool Whip, strawberries, banana, Hershey's syrup (drizzled).

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Mix eggs, flour, sugar and Sweet 'N Low together.
Add remaining ingredients, except margarine.
Melt the margarine in pie dish and add mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in loaf pan.
Crumble 1 pack of Ritz crackers on top, pour 1/2 stick margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in pineapple juice for several hours.
Grill chicken along with the pineapple slices.

title: half pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder, mace and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: wedding coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour angel food pan.
Pour part of mixture into pan.
Sprinkle on crushed nuts and cinnamon.
Add rest of batter.
Mix brown sugar and crushed nuts; sprinkle on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: jalapeno-buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine buttermilk and jalapeno chilies in small bowl; cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 475°.
Place flour in a large bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender or fork until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Dough will be soft and wet.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a floured 1 1/2-inch cutter without twisting.
Re-roll remaining dough and repeat cutting procedure.
Place biscuits, sides nearly touching, on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.

title: chicken soup
directions: Stew whole chicken or chicken pieces in water seasoned with salt and lemon pepper.
Remove chicken and bring broth to a boil. Stir in broken-up vermicelli and small meatballs made from ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight and skim fat from top.
Serve in soup bowls.
Chicken can be used in another recipe.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until soft.
Combine all other ingredients, except sauce, and fill shells.
Lay in casserole dish and cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until noodles feel soft.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven
as
per box instructions.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt 1 stick butter in oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle brown
sugar
evenly
across
pan.
Place
pineapple slices along edges and in center of pan with cherries inserted in their holes. Save the juice from the pineapple and substitute it for the water in the cake batter.
Prepare cake batter as box
instructs.
Pour evenly
across
pineapple
layer and bake.
Cake
is
done
when toothpick comes out clean.
Allow cake to cool.
Loosen edges and turn out.
Ready to serve.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or 5 to 6 hours on high. Serve over rice or noodles. Yummy!

title: hot potato salad
directions: In a skillet put vinegar, sugar and eggs.
Mix well and bring to boil, stirring continually.
Pour over remaining ingredients. If dry, stir in a few tablespoons of mayonnaise.
Is good cold, too.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables and mix well. Place in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Serve cold.

title: creamsicle pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature. Beat with electric mixer until very soft and creamy. Mix with thawed Cool Whip; blend until creamy. Add orange juice and blend with mixer until thoroughly incorporated. Set aside.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Melt in double boiler, then add the cocoa and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on 2 waxed paper lined cookie sheets.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken bake
directions: Cut chicken up.
Place in pan; pour soup over chicken and pour half and half over.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll into ball and bake until brown.

title: fancy slaw(serves 8 or more)
directions: Cook noodles.
Combine with cabbage, onions and 2 kinds of seeds.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and packet of spices from noodles in a small jar and mix well.
Pour over cabbage. Serve cold.

title: polish bread(babka)
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over sugar and butter.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast cake in 1/3 cup warm water.
Add this to the milk mixture. Add the flour and mix this well.
Add salt to eggs and beat until thick.
Add to mixture and mix this good.
Knead for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cover and let rise 3 to 4 hours at room temperature. Punch down and put in loaf pans and let rise again about 1 hour. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook for 1/2 hour after hard boil; put into jars and seal or freeze when cool.

title: quick buckwheat cakes
directions: Dissolve yeast well in warm water.
Add salt and molasses. Stir in flour.
Beat well.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake on hot griddle.
Makes 12 cakes.

title: crunchy chews
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in large saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in peanut butter.
Add nuts and cereal.
Stir in evenly.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut squares while cool.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut nuts, dates and orange slices in small pieces; add coconut. Melt margarine and pour over mixture.
In another bowl beat eggs and sugar; add sifted flour to soda and milk.
Pour over nut mixture and mix well.
Grease and flour a large tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 hours.
Let cool for 10 minutes before removing.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with a small amount of the milk.
Add rest of the milk.
Cook over boiling water (in a double boiler), stirring until thick.
Cover; cook for 15 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Add a small amount of the hot mixture to the egg yolks.
Pour back and cook a few minutes longer.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour filling into baked shell.
Cool slightly; cover with meringue.

title: oriental vegetables and rice
directions: Preheat vegetable oil; saute chicken strips until light brown. Remove from skillet; saute rice until light golden.
Pour off excess oil.
Add 2 1/2 cups warm water, low sodium salt, garlic powder and browned chicken strips.
When water boils, reduce to lower heat and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes, or until rice is done. Add soy sauce, mushrooms
and the frozen vegetables.
Remove from heat; stir lightly.
Serve with iced tea.

title: french apple pie
directions: Beat butter, sugar and egg together well.
Add rest of ingredients except apples.
Prepare bottom pie shell and arrange apples in pie and pour batter over apples and top with the following.

title: emily's favorite dirty rice
directions: Use 2 parts Sprite or 7-Up to 1 part grape juice (red or white).
You can make an ice ring with grapes in it to help keep it cold.
Cherries can also be used.

title: banana cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Spoon sliced bananas into 11x7x2 inch baking pan or pan of approximate size. Combine sugar with the flour. Sprinkle over bananas. Combine milk and
vanilla. Pour into pan. Dot with butter. Cover with crust.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in order given with pastry blender. Add egg, water and vinegar.
This makes 1 pie crust.

title: nacho dip supreme
directions: On a large, flat dish (a regular dinner plate works well), spread sour cream to the edge.
Continue to layer remaining ingredients in order.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour cut corn, creamed corn and cornstarch into a large mixing bowl.
Then add slightly beaten eggs, sugar, salt, milk and butter or margarine.
Fold and mix ingredients well.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temp., add onions, garlic, salt, and mayo. Mix well. After removing all seeds from cucumber, grate and drain, then add to mixture and stir well. Spread on 8 slices of bread and top with remaining bread, then cut into 4 pieces each. Makes 32 mini sandwiches.

title: better than a kiss cake
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in remaining items.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked ham
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice; set aside. Place ham in baking pan; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, cloves, mustard and vinegar in small bowl.
Stir in reserved pineapple juice.
Score meat before placing pineapple slices on top of ham.
Spoon glaze over pineapple and ham.
Bake another 40 to 45 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: cottage pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops, both sides, then take chops out of pan and set aside.
Add water to pan where chops were fried, to deglaze the pan.
Layer all vegetables in large casserole.
Put pork chops on top of vegetables, add salt and pepper, now pour glazing water over all ingredients.
Bake at 350° with foil laying loosely over top for first 30 minutes, remove foil and bake uncovered 30 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chop bake
directions: In a large skillet, brown chops, then drain.
In greased 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes, then pork chops. Thoroughly blend soup mix with water and pour over top.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour (or until potatoes are tender) in preheated 350° oven.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Combine shrimp, eggs, onions, butter, cornstarch, salt and sugar in a blender container or food processor bowl.
Process to a paste consistency.
Stir in water chestnuts.
Trim bread of crusts and cut into triangles.
Spread with shrimp mixture.
In a frying pan, heat 1-inch oil to 400°.
Fry toast, shrimp side down, until golden.
Turn and continue frying until bread side is brown. Drain and serve warm.
Freezes well fully prepared.
Reheat at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 32.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, salt, sugar and baking soda in a large bowl.
Heat liquids until very warm.
Add to dry mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into pans. Sprinkle tops with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool on racks.

title: sugar peas in pod(sukkererter)
directions: Wash pods and string them.
Cut diagonally in 1-inch lengths. Cover with salted water and boil until tender.
Drain and save 1 cup of liquid.
Make a white sauce from butter, flour and liquid. Add sugar and salt.
Add chopped parsley and stir into peas. Serves 6.

title: lakeshore party punch
directions: Boil 20 cups water and tea 10 minutes and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Crush wafers.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well by hand. Mold into a log.
Place on platter and refrigerate.
Chill and slice before serving.

title: cranberry souffle salad
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and salt thoroughly in small saucepan.
Add water and place over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatine is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in mayonnaise, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Blend with a rotary beater.
Pour into a refrigerator tray.
Quick chill in freezer unit 10 to 15 minutes or until firm, 1-inch from edge, but soft in center.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli-rice dish
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Saute broccoli and onion in margarine.
Add soups, milk, rice and half of cheese and mix together.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, and 1/2 hour uncovered.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix by hand.
Do not use electric mixer.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Then add last 3 ingredients and mix well. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° until light brown and filling is firm, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: surprise salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: five layer dinner
directions: In a casserole dish, put a layer of hamburger, layer of onions, layer of potatoes, layer of green pepper and layer of tomatoes. Layer again, ending with tomatoes, combined with 1/2 cup of water for the last layer.
Bake at 325°.

title: quick fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with marshmallow cream and lemon juice.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in water.
Cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer. stir a little of hot mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add to remaining hot mixture in top of double boiler and cook for 2 minutes over hot water stirring constantly.
Add butter, cool - add lemon rind and juice.
Pour into baked shell, cover with meringue. Bake 325 for 15 minutes.

title: carnitas with red sauce
directions: Fry meat until crunchy and brown.
Add tomato sauce and picante sauce to meat.
Then season it with onion and garlic salt. Serve with rice and beans, tortillas and some guacamole!
Very fast and good!

title: nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have shortening at room temperature. Grease and flour loaf pan or muffin tins.
Sift flour before measuring.
Mash shortening and sift in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and 3/4 milk.
Mix until flour is dampened, then beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining milk and eggs.
Beat 1 minute.
Add nuts and bake 1 hour for loaf pan or 20 to 30 minutes for muffin tins.

title: salad galore
directions: Shred lettuce and cabbage.
Cut in small pieces celery, onions, tomatoes, broccoli, cauliflower and apple.
Grate carrots and cheese.
Cut Jicama into 1-inch strips.
Wash beans off.
Add all together and serve with your favorite dressing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put 1/4 package of stuffing mix in baking dish.
Mix squash, carrots, onion, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper and part oleo. Pour this over stuffing.
Put 1/4 stuffing mix on top.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Combine ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 5 hours.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix with beef or chicken and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: lo-cal chicken rellenos
directions: Coat chicken in flour and saute in oil until light brown.
Add a little water or chicken broth and simmer until done.
In another pan, simmer onion and garlic with tomatoes until onion is soft and tomatoes start to thicken.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in large buttered casserole.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/4 cup butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add boiling water until of desired liquid.
Do not over add water.
Mix well and add vanilla.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: end of garden soup
directions: Chop into large pieces the first 5 ingredients.
(Note that summer squash, eggplant and green pepper can be added or substituted for the veggies listed.)
Brown onion, shallot and pressed garlic.
Add tomatoes; stir.
Add other veggies, stirring and slightly browning.
Add stock, bay leaf, salt and pepper. Cover and let simmer until veggies are slightly undercooked.
Add basil, cayenne and paprika and simmer for 15 minutes more.
Put through food mill or blender to break down, but not mush after bay leaf is removed.
Serve hot or cold with good bread.
Excess can be jarred and eventually frozen.
Yield:
24 to 30 cups.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: In a bowl, combine the peppers, Tabasco and salt.
Whisk in the olive oil and lemon juice.
Add the shrimp and toss to cover. Cover the bowl and refrigerate for at least 3 and up to 24 hours before cooking.

title: peanut loaf
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Place in small loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Great with milk for after school snack.

title: angel food torte
directions: Cut angel food cake into cubes. Prepare chocolate pudding according to pie directions. Then add in Cool Whip (folding gently). Layer angel food cake on bottom of a tall glass container, then spoon over top the pudding mixture. Crush up the Oreo cookies and sprinkle on top of pudding. Repeat all these steps as many times as you desire for a beautiful layered look.

title: pie crust(double 8 or 9-inch)
directions: Mix flour and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cut Crisco into flour with 2 knives or pastry blender until mixture is uniform and very fine.
Sprinkle water over mixture, a tablespoonful at a time, tossing lightly with a fork.
When all water has been added and mixed, work dough into a firm ball with hands.
Press dough into a flat circle.
Roll on a lightly floured board or pastry cloth 1/8-inch thick.
Cut crust to extend 1/2 inch beyond edge of pie plate.
If shell is to be baked with no filling, prick bottom and sides with fork before baking.
Bake in a hot 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil sliced squash until done.
Cut up onion into squash.
Add eggs, cornbread crumbs, mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
All of this mixed together should have the consistency of dressing.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: tuna vegetable salad
directions: Drain and mix; chill.
You can use any salad dressing or vinegar, sugar and oil mixed.
This is what I prefer.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo, add oil and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in moderate oven (350°).
Makes 6 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, zucchini, oil, and eggs together. Add flour, powder, soda, cinnamon, salt and nuts. Pour into greased floured pan. Bake 1- 1 1/2 hrs. At 350 degrees.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Line a 15 x 9 x 1-inch pan with aluminum foil. Arrange graham crackers on foil; set aside. Combine margarine and sugar in medium saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add cinnamon and nuts. Pour over crackers, spreading to coat evenly. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool 5 minutes. Using spatula, separate and place on waxed
paper-lined cookie sheets. Store in refrigerator between sheets of waxed paper.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix together drained pineapple and marshmallows, then set aside.
Mix together next 5 ingredients and cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool thoroughly.
Fold into custard, pineapple and marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight. Fold in apples, peanuts and Cool Whip the next day.

title: oreo supreme
directions: Crush the Oreo cookies.
Mix together with the melted oleo and pat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan for a crust.
Chill.
Cream Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over chilled crust and refrigerate.
Blend chocolate pudding, vanilla pudding and milk. Pour over first layer and chill.
Cover with Cool Whip and then crushed Oreo cookies.
Chill before serving.

title: apples in a jar (for pies)
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch 20 minutes; add cinnamon and lemon juice. Peel and slice apples; pack in sterile jars. Pour hot syrup over apples to 1 inch of top of jar.
Seal and process in water bath for 20 minutes after it starts to boil.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add the saved pineapple juice and stir. Add pineapple and cheese.
Mix and place in casserole dish. Crumble Ritz crackers over top and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Great with ham.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour, salt and cocoa in large pan. Combine egg yolks and 1 cup milk.
Combine with dry ingredients. Add other cup of milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mix in butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pastry shell.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut seeded tomato into small pieces and add to mixture before serving.

title: chicken linguine
directions: Saute mushrooms in sherry and 1 tablespoon margarine in a nonstick skillet 5 minutes.

title: lemon lush pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Beat pudding mix with milk. Spread over cheese mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: fettuccine with ham and peas
directions: Saute garlic in 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Stir in shredded ham and peas.
Saute over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and keep warm.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions, omitting salt.
Drain well, plac in a large serving bowl.
Add 1/2 cup softened butter, stirring until completely melted.
Add Parmesan cheese and sour cream, stirring gently to coat well.
Fold ham mixture into fettuccine mixture.
Add pepper, toss gently.
Serve immediately. Yields 6 servings.

title: oven-fried picnic chicken
directions: Rinse chicken pieces; pat dry with paper towels.
Set aside. In small bowl stir together crackers, peanuts and paprika.
Spread mixture on sheet of waxed paper.
In another bowl combine the egg and milk.
Dip each chicken piece in egg mixture, then roll in crumb mixture to coat thoroughly.
Arrange chicken, skin side up, in baking dish.
Do not let them touch.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 50 minutes or until tender.
Do not turn.
Cool on paper towels.

title: chicken breasts delux
directions: Grease large baking dish and spread beef (chopped) in dish. Wrap each chicken breast with a bacon slice and arrange in dish over beef. Spread undiluted soup over chicken. Cover with foil and bake in preheated 300° oven for 2 hours. Remove foil. Add mushrooms and continue baking at 350° for 30 minutes. Baste as needed.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Follow directions on Jell-O box.
Mix ingredients and gel.

title: purple cow
directions: Place milk, grape juice concentrate and 2 scoops of vanilla ice cream in blender container.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into two 12 ounce glasses.
Top with scoops of vanilla ice cream.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; mix other ingredients.
Add dry to wet mixture gradually.	Beat
until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blow-out patch pancakes
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When once selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.

title: chicken breasts 'n wild rice
directions: Cook wild rice following basic method just until kernels open slightly (30 to 40 minutes).
Spread rice in buttered 8 x 12-inch oblong baking dish.
Combine soup, sour cream, undrained mushrooms and sherry.
Pour about 1/2 of the soup mixture over rice. Remove skin from chicken breasts.
Arrange breasts over soup. Spoon remaining soup mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake until heated through, about 30 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: real good salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: garlic butter spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spread on bread and toast or crackers, too. YUM!

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix chopped peppers, onion, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil 2 minutes.
Set off heat and add Certo.
Let stand 5 minutes, then pour into jars.
Use small jars.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, 1/2 cup cheese, olives, onions and salt.
Use enough salad dressing to moisten and toss lightly. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; sprinkle remaining cheese and chips on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: chili
directions: In large pot, saute veggies and brown meat; drain oil.
Add tomatoes, spices and kidney beans; mix well.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes until most of liquid is absorbed.

title: fried chicken
directions: Trim chicken. Dip into eggs, then into bread crumbs. Fry in heated oil on medium heat, until brown. Turn and brown other side. Drain on paper towels. Serves 4. Enjoy!

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together in jar (dry).
When ready to use, mix 2 or 3 teaspoons in 1 cup water.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Mix all ingredients (if dry, add cream); mix well.
Put in crab shells; top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: chocolate dream cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into mixing bowl; blend well.
Bring to rapid boil in saucepan the margarine, shortening, water and cocoa. Pour over flour-sugar mixture and mix well.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Put ingredients into mixing bowl.
Slowly add salad oil and beat until thick emulsion forms.
Add 1/6 cup more vinegar and celery seed.
Store in refrigerator in a jar.
Delicious!

title: sticky rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: lazy day fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: quick crab bisque
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Heat in a double boiler for 15 minutes and serve.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and oil together.
Add eggs and milk.
Sift flour and soda together and add it to the mixture.
Mix in boiling water.
Pour into a greased and floured cake pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Put all vegetables in soup pot.
Cover with stock (also may use water or half water and half stock).
Cover and cook for 1/2 hour to 2 1/2 hours, depends on how done you like your vegetables.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Place all in blender and blend until well mixed.

title: red satin punch
directions: Chill juices and 7-Up.
Make two trays of ice cubes with 7-Up. At serving time, combine cranberry and apple juice in a punch bowl.
Slowly pour in 7-Up.
Add 7-Up ice cubes.
Makes 35 cups.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Prepare corn bread according to your normal recipe.
Stir in ingredients.
Cook according to cornbread temperature and time.

title: mother's pecan cake
directions: Pour wine over nuts the night before.
Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Sift flour with spice.
Add alternately with buttermilk to other mixture.
Add well beaten egg whites.
Fold in flour-dredged fruit and nuts. Place batter in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Steam 3 hours, then dry off in oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken cornelia
directions: Wash chicken pieces and dry with paper towel.
Season as desired.
Place in large Pyrex so pieces will not be on top of one another.
Mix mushroom soup and evaporated milk.
Spoon mixture over chicken and sprinkle with parsley.
Do not cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until chicken is tender.

title: texas peanut brittlelow calorie dishes
directions: Butter heavily 2 cookie sheets.
Put into a saucepan the sugar, water and corn syrup. Bring to a boil. Boil until you hold up a spoon and it spins a thread.
Add peanuts.
Cook and stir until the peanuts turn a brownish gold.
Remove from heat. Stir in margarine, salt and soda. Pour into cookie sheets to cool and harden. Break into pieces.

title: coconut pudding
directions: In a large sauce pan combine coconut milk and milk.
Blend together sugar and cornstarch and stir into coconut milk mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture thickens. Pour into a 8 inch square baking pan.
Chill. When firm cut into small squares or triangles.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, shortening and pumpkin.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix in a large pot and store in an airtight container.
Use 1/3 to 1/2 cup in a mug and add boiling water.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in mixture of salad dressing, jam and onion soup mix.
Pour leftover mixture over chicken pieces and bake uncovered at 275° for 2 hours.

title: veggie rotini salad
directions: Cook rotini and drain.
Mix everything in a bowl and chill.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peppermint bark
directions: Melt chocolate in heatproof bowl over hot, not boiling, water. Remove from heat and stir in crushed candy canes.
Spread in thin layer on waxed paper.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to package instructions for pie filling, but use only 2 cups of milk instead of 4.
Make certain you beat it only one minute on low speed.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: orange cheesecake(lo-cal; lo-fat)
directions: Spray a 9-inch pie pan with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle on the graham cracker crumbs. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stirring well. Let it cool, then put gelatin, cottage cheese and cream cheese in blender. Blend on medium. Pour into a large bowl and fold in whipped topping. Pour into prepared pie pan. Smooth over top and refrigerate. Garnish with peeled orange slices. Delicious!

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: special k fruit cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside. Place margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix until thoroughly combined.
Mix in coconut, nuts, raisins and Special K cereal.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 1 unbaked pie shell.
Top with other unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spanish pot roast
directions: Brown meat in oil until loses pink.
Add everything except rice.
Simmer 2 hours; stir occasionally.
Add rice and simmer 1 more hour.
Stir occasionally.
If becomes dry before rice is done, then add more water.
Cook in large Dutch oven size pan. Cook covered.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
A little brown sugar and hot sauce can be added to suit taste.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini until done.
Add cucumber, tomatoes and 3/4 bottle of dressing and 1/2 jar Salad Supreme.
Marinate overnight. Add remainder of dressing.

title: brunch bake(serves 6)
directions: Cook bacon.
Let cool and crumble.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: dry orange salad
directions: Pour cottage cheese into a bowl and add the dry orange jello. Stir well.
Add the drained mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks. Mix and add the miniature marshmallows.
Put into refrigerator and let set overnight.
Serve alone or on lettuce leaves.

title: betty jo's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients or blend in blender a few minutes.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Don't brown.

title: fruit salad dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip and condensed milk with electric mixer.
Fold in pineapple and cherry pie filling until pink in color.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter or margarine and cream cheese until smooth. Add sugar and cream together until smooth and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, blending until smooth.
Sift flour and add to mixture.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Pour into a 12-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Allow cake to cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan and continue to cool.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Slice onions and cucumbers very thin.
Soak in salt water 2 to 3 hours.
Rinse well.
Add sugar and vinegar; freeze.

title: choco chip zucchini cake
directions: Combine sugar, butter and oil with the eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with buttermilk.
Fold in zucchini, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar when cool.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine sausage, bread crumbs and egg; mix thoroughly.
Fill each mushroom cap with mixture.
Put on a buttered broiler pan and broil about 6 inches from heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until sizzling.

title: orient express chicken breasts
directions: Heat the oil in a saucepan, add onion, ginger and oyster sauce.
Pour sauce on the chicken breasts and let stand for 5 minutes.
While sauteeing, add the marinated chicken breasts.
Save the marinade of teriyaki sauce.
Stir
the chicken to coat with the sauteed ingredients.
Keep covered for 25 minutes and simmer. Add soy sauce and remaining marinade.
Let boil.
Season to taste. Add snow peas and coriander in the last few minutes of cooking. Serve hot.

title: slaw or potato salad dressing
directions: Mix everything together except mayonnaise.
Cook until thick, then add mayonnaise and beat well.
Cool before using.
Makes more than a quart.
Stores well in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Shred zucchini like cabbage, using rind also.
If seeds are really big, remove, otherwise can leave them.
Combine zucchini with all other ingredients.
Can add nuts or raisins to your desire.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt butter in large pan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or wax paper, press mixture evenly into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cut into squares when cool.
Use fresh marshmallows.

title: steamed dinner
directions: Peel potatoes and slice lengthwise.
Sprinkle with ground pepper and salt.
Steam for 8 to 10 minutes (until done).
Wash and trim ends off zucchini.
Slice lengthwise.
Sprinkle dill and pepper on top.
Steam for 4 to 5 minutes (until done).
Wash and trim leaves and bottom off leek.
Cut very thin strips about 3 inches long.
Wash mushrooms and cut into fourths.
Roll lemon well and cut in half.
Juice.
Warm 1 teaspoon of olive oil in pan. Sprinkle leek strips in pan.
Pour mushrooms over leeks.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon dill and 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper.
Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice and increase heat.
Add 1/3 cup Chablis or white wine. Shake mixture slightly.
Place halibut on top of mixture.
Sprinkle sea salt and ground pepper over fish.
Put lid on and steam until done.

title: green mountain gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, molasses and egg and mix thoroughly.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients.
Roll in small balls; dip in granulated sugar and place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: pecan dream bars(these were melinda runcie's favorite)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Place grits in boiling water, cook 2-5 minutes. Add butter, cheese roll, and velveeta cheese, melt together, then add 2 beaten eggs with milk. Pour mixture into baking dish. Bake 45-60 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cut and mix all ingredients together as follows:
Cook shells, drain, run under cold water until cooled.
Cut all ingredients into chunks.
Mix oil, vinegar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Pour over salad; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Better flavor if it sets for a few hours.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Drain lettuce well and spread evenly in flat bottom container. Add in layers the celery, onion, carrots, green peppers and frozen peas.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar.
Spread over peas.
Sprinkle bacon and Cheddar cheese over mayonnaise mixture. Cover with Saran Wrap (tightly) and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix
and
bring to a boil all ingredients except cucumbers; then add cucumbers.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Keep stirring until cucumbers change color.
Then pack into jars and seal.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir all together and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: bread-in-a-bag
directions: In a 1 gallon reclosable bag, add 1/2 cup flour, yeast, sugar and warm water.
Mix thoroughly by squeezing the zipped bag.
Let rest 10 minutes (in sun if possible).
Add to the bag whole wheat flour, 1/2 cup flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and oil.
Knead the bag, adding 1/2 cup flour (or as needed) to make dough pull away from bag into a ball.
Turn bag inside out so dough drops onto floured wax paper.
Knead into loaf shape and place in greased pan.
Cover with the plastic bag; let rise 30 minutes in warm place.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press crescent rolls in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Hidden Valley dressing.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle veggies over cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pat down firmly.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix all together; pour into greased casserole dish.
You can put buttered Ritz cracker crumbs on top. Heat in oven at 400° until bubbly or top is browned.

title: chicken cordon bleu basket(microwave recipe)
directions: Pound chicken breasts thin.
Lay a strip of ham and slice of cheese on each breast half.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks. Dip in slightly beaten egg white (or water, if preferred) and roll in bread crumbs to coat.
Place in microwavable casserole dish. Microwave approximately 10 to 12 minutes, turning once halfway through.
Serve over a bed of rice.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients into a large bowl; blend well with a spoon.
Pour into a long Pyrex dish and chill before serving.

title: banana nut bread(makes 12 cupcakes or 1 loaf)
directions: Mix in order given.
Grease a loaf pan.
Put mixture in one loaf or 12 lined cupcake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for paper lined cupcakes or 1 hour for loaf pan.

title: burox
directions: Make yeast dough into muffin size balls.
Roll dough out until paper thin.
Fry ground beef and drain.
Cook cabbage and drain. Add ground beef and cabbage together. Spoon texture out into rolled dough.
Add 1/2 slice cheese on top.
Make into a biscuit. Put "biscuit" in greased pan.
Let raise until doubled in size. Brush with oil on top before baking.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sausage stars
directions: Mix sausage, cheeses, red pepper and olives in a bowl.
Then spray muffin tins with Pam and press wontons in tin.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Remove wontons from tins.
Put on cookie sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture and bake another 5 minutes or until bubbles.
Serve warm.

title: granny cake
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients and then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Put crushed corn flakes, if desired, on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie shell; bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
(This will also make 15 miniature pie shells.)

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish spread crescent rolls on the bottom.
Crumble cooked sausage over rolls.
Spread hash browns then the cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk and salt and pepper. Pour over casserole and bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.	Make sure it is brown.
I usually make this the night before and pour the egg/milk mixture over the rest of it prior to baking.
This is a great casserole for Christmas morning!

title: no sugar pie
directions: Mix water and cornstarch.
Heat until very thick.
Add sugar free jello.
Line pie crust with strawberries or sliced peaches. Pour thickened gel over top.
Chill and serve with any sugar free topping.

title: lore's zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Turn batter into a well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake one hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: asparagus casserole supreme
directions: Grate cheese and mix well with cracker crumbs.
Add liquid from asparagus to mushroom soup.
Put layer of cracker crumbs and cheese in bottom of casserole; add layer of asparagus tips. Sprinkle with nuts.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Put layer of cheese and cracker crumbs on top; decorate with whole blanched almonds or pecans.
Pour melted butter over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: You can also add onions, tomatoes, green pepper, lettuce, etc., whatever you desire.
Arrange roll dough in bottom of 9-inch pie shell to form crust.
Brown ground beef.
Drain well.
Add taco seasoning.
(Do not add any water to the seasoning mix.)
Put meat into pie.
Spread sour cream over.
If desired, slice tomatoes, green peppers, onion and lettuce on pie.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pepsi over ice
directions: Pour Pepsi into cup over ice.

title: love letters
directions: Mix chicken, cheese and seasonings.
Some add a little cream cheese to help hold mixture together.
Place 1 teaspoon of mixture on wonton wrapper and fold like an envelope.
Wet edges with a touch of water to seal envelope.
Deep fry until golden.
Serve with sweet and sour dip.

title: fresh broccoli medley
directions: Toss together the broccoli, bacon, raisins, sunflower seeds and onion.
Mix together the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix the mayonnaise mixture with the broccoli mixture.
Chill.

title: oven green beans
directions: Place beans in 9 x 13 pan. Drizzle with oil and remaining ingredients. Stir to coat. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Stir midway.

title: ranger krispies(cookies)
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco, sugar and brown sugar and then add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Add noodles to boiling, salted water; cook until tender. Drain and rinse.
Mix all ingredients and put in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ministicks
directions: Blend together dry ingredients in a shallow dish.
Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk.
Shake to remove excess.
Roll in flour mixture. Heat oil or shortening 1-inch deep in electric skillet. Add chicken pieces a few at a time.
Cook until golden brown on both sides, turning once, about 5 minutes altogether.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot or cold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain off excess grease. Begin with layer of squash (half).
Add beef mixture, then rest of squash. Pour can of undiluted soup on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove 1/2 cup of cookie dough and reserve for another use.
Add flour to remaining dough and knead with hands to combine.
Press dough into 14-inch circle pizza pan. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until cookie is lightly browned. Let cool 10 minutes.
Loosen cookie from pan and cool completely.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix and pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze.

title: hot fudge dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Add vanilla and set aside to cool. Crush cookies; add melted oleo and press into a 9 x 13 pan. Freeze for 20 minutes. Spread 1/2 gallon of ice cream over crust and freeze for another 30 minutes. Pour cooled fudge sauce over the ice cream and freeze another 30 minutes. Spread 8-ounce carton of Cool Whip on top; cover with foil and freeze for 12 hours.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire, lemon juice and seasonings.

title: chinese noodle cookies
directions: Boil sugar, Karo syrup and margarine for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter; make sure it melts.
Add vanilla and Chinese noodles.
Fill miniature paper cups.
Work fast, as mixture becomes difficult to work with as it cools off.

title: veal parmesan with spaghetti
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Remove meat; add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in next 7 ingredients; add meat. Cover; simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Remove 1/2 the sauce from heat; stir into spaghetti.
Top cutlets with cheese; cover pan for 5 minutes.
Arrange spaghetti and meat on platter.
Pass extra sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken cubes in a 7 x 11-inch casserole dish.

title: paul lynde's beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook, covered, 6 to 7 hours minimum in a 250° oven.

title: cherry spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add buttermilk, soda and applesauce.
Sift flour with baking powder and spices. Add to creamed mixture.
Mix the cherries and nuts with a little bit of flour and add to the mixture.
Cook in layers and put together with 7 Minute Icing.

title: oyster dressing(turkey stuffing)
directions: Saute sausage; remove.
Add margarine.
Saute onions, celery and parsley (add garlic if you like).
Remove from heat; add salt and pepper, Worcestershire sauce, oysters, sausage, pecans and bread and toss well.
Makes 10 to 12 cups.
Stuff turkey or bake in separate pan.

title: raspberry ripple
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, butter, sugar and salt.
Blend with pastry blender until resembles coarse meal.
Add egg yolk and work dough with hands until dough forms a ball.
Divide into thirds on greased cookie sheet.
Shape each third into a 12 x 1-inch strip about 4-inches apart.
Make depression 1/2-inch deep down the middle of each strip.

title: ice magic
directions: Pour juice into ice cube tray. Place a toothpick into each section. Freeze.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, 1 Tbsp milk and sugar in a large bowl whisk until smooth. Gently stir in the whipped topping. Spread in the bottom of the cracker crust. Pour 1 cup milk into a bowl, add pudding mixes. Beat with a wire whisk for 1 minute, it will be thick. Whisk in pumpkin and spices until well blended. Spread over cheese layer. Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set. Garnish with extra topping if desired. Store left over pie in the refrigerator.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion.
Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer 3 hours; salt to taste.

title: cool lime pie
directions: Cream together softened cream cheese with the condensed milk. Add limeade and food coloring until very smooth. Fold in half the carton of Cool Whip and place filling in the prepared crust. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before topping with remaining Cool Whip, kiwi and oranges.

title: candy topped crispy pops
directions: Place entire contents of box of cereal in very large bowl. Over low heat, melt margarine and marshmallows until smooth and mixed.
Pour this mix over cereal and stir gently, coating.
Divide and press gently into two foil or wax papered 13 x 9-inch edged cookie sheets.
Let cool.
Flip onto cutting board and cut bars approximately 2 x 3 x 3/4-inch thick.
Insert sticks 2/3 through bars.
Melt chocolate chips and dip 1/3 of each in, then sprinkle with candy.
Cool on wax paper.
Can be individually wrapped and tied with ribbon.

title: willie mae's broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
The batter is thick.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits, butter and cheese in salted water until well done. Add egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites.
Put in greased casserole. Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: First, you need to cook the chicken while fixing the dough. Put both together in a big pan; stir on the stove.
Cook until dough is real soft and the chicken is real tender, about 20 to 25 minutes on low on the top of the stove.

title: granola
directions: Blend liquid ingredients.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Crumble and bake on cookie sheets at 350° for 15 minutes.
Lower to 200° and bake until dry and golden brown.
Stir occasionally.
Keeps well stored in covered jars.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add mashed bananas, sour cream and baking soda. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; slowly add.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, peanut butter and sugars.
Add eggs, creaming well.
Add to mixture the soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add chips and M&M's.
Add oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 16 minutes.
These must be soft on top when done baking.
Let set on pan for a few seconds before removing.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place 3 cups chopped cabbage in casserole dish.
In skillet, put hamburger, onion, butter, salt and pepper.
Let cook until brown.
Pour over cabbage.
Place remaining cabbage on meat mixture.
Spread tomato soup over cabbage.
Let cook, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Gradually add flour, egg yolk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Place on buttered cookie sheet and pat down until 1/4-inch thick.
Spread unbeaten egg white over top of cookie mixture.
Pour off excess egg white.
Sprinkle nuts on top and press into cookies.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Add water to egg white.
Add pecan halves and toss to coat. In separate bowl mix well the cinnamon, sugar and salt.
Pour over nuts and egg white mixture.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes until dry.

title: crunchy baked chicken
directions: Crush cornflakes in a food processor or with a rolling pin. Put in a plastic bag large enough to place a piece of chicken in. Add parsley and garlic to the bag.
Set aside.
Using a brush coat the chicken all over with the Miracle Whip.
Place one piece at a time into the bag of cornflakes and shake until well coated.
Place in a pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Continue with the other pieces.
Place in 325° oven, uncovered, and bake for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In bowl mix flour and baking powder. With pastry blender (or a fork), cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Add milk and stir enough to hold dough together.
Place on floured board, knead lightly about 10 times. Roll dough 1/2 inch thick.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture and raisins.
Roll up into log shape. Cut into 3/4-inch pieces.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: bride's cake
directions: Beat in whites and acid of green lemon.
Double for one and a half pound cake.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: sweet-sour dressing
directions: Put all in blender and blend until sugar is dissolved.
Shake before using.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush wafers, melt margarine and orange juice.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll
into
small balls and coat with additional powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: quick root beer
directions: Dissolve the sugar in some hot water, then combine it with the rest of the ingredients.
Put the mixture into jars, cover them and set them in the sun for 4 hours.
The root beer will be ready to serve the next day.
Chill it before serving.

title: lemon dessert(lucky if any's left)
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, mix flour, oleo and nuts. Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Put sugar and can of condensed milk in a large mixing bowl. Pour in blender and beat on high.
Then empty in the freezer and add the rest of the ingredients.

title: doughnuts
directions: Put holes in each biscuit, stretching the holes until the edges only are full of dough.
Fry in oil; turn each when bottoms look brown.
Place each doughnut in bag and shake in cinnamon mixture.
Pull out with fork.
These cook rapidly, so watch closely.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in a 2-quart dish (8 x 12-inches).
Place margarine in a 2 quart glass bottom bowl; microwave on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in dry cake mix and granola.
Blend well.
Sprinkle this crumb mixture over pie filling.
Microwave on High 12 or 14 minutes, rotating halfway through cooking.
Top crumb mixture will become crisp upon standing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon, pears and pineapple congealed salad
directions: Combine 3/4 cup of the pear juice and 1/4 cup of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O and stir well. Cool to touch.
Blend buttermilk with Cool Whip.
Add mayonnaise (or sour cream) and blend well.
Fold in the fruit and grated cheese.
Add cooled Jell-O and blend well.
Congeal in 3-quart Pyrex dish. Cut into 18 pieces.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix eggs, mushrooms soup, diced onions and mayonnaise in bowl. Add broccoli.
Mix and put in baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese, Italian or Cheddar, amount to taste.
Put buttered bread crumbs over cheese.
Bake at 350° in oven until golden brown and sides look as if they are bubbling.

title: cranberry pineapple mold
directions: Make Jell-O with one cup hot and one cup cold water.
Stir in cranberry sauce, crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add walnuts.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mash garlic, salt, and pepper with fork.
Add anchory paste, then mash again.
Add mustard, Worcestershire sauce and 2 T Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Beat in oil, lemon juice, and vinegar until well blended.
Beat in oil, lemon juice, and vinegar until well blended.
Beat in egg yolks until thick and creamy.
Add to lettuce sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Enjoy!
You could also add grilled chic-shrimp or even steak.

title: corn chowder
directions: In 5-quart pan brown bacon pieces.
Drain off grease.
Add potatoes and corn.
Cover with water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add oleo and Cremora; stir.
Thicken with potato flakes.

title: punch
directions: Heat sugar and water to boiling to melt sugar and cool.
Mix all ingredients together in a milk carton and freeze.
Thaw 2 hours before serving.
Add two 2-liter bottles Sprite and serve slushy.
Delicious!!!!!!

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix above ingredients in a large bowl until well blended (except cherries).
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
In the center of each cookie, place a cherry.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: no fat chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pans.
Heat milk until barely simmering.
Remove from heat and whisk in cocoa until thickened and almost smooth.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes to cool.
Whisk in applesauce and vanilla.
Mix flour, 1 1/4 cups sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Beat egg whites in medium bowl until thick and foamy.
Gradually beat in remaining 1/4 cup sugar until stiff peaks form.
Pour cocoa mixture over flour mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Gently stir about 1/4 egg whites into flour.
Fold in remaining whites until no streaks remain.
Pour into pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack about 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: stuffed bass or flounder
directions: Season fish with salt.
Saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add wine or chicken bouillon and milk.
Stir until thick.
Add shrimp, crab, bread crumbs, parsley and egg.
Season with salt and pepper and cayenne pepper.
Place stuffing on fish fillets and roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Place in buttered baking pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Brush with remaining butter and sprinkle with paprika and lemon juice.
Bake uncovered for 10 minutes.
Spoon pan juices over fish and serve.
Serve with a tossed salad and corn muffins.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Season chicken, roll in butter.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients.
Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Defrost green beans.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Put layer of green beans on bottom of dish.
Cover with sour cream and soup mix.
Slice Velveeta cheese and put on top.
Cover with Durkee onions.
Repeat with another layer.
Top with slivered almonds or ground almonds.
Bake in conventional oven or microwave until cheese is melted.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 cake pan and bake according to directions on box.
Cool cake.
Drain pineapple and mix pineapple juice with pudding.
Mix in pineapple and cool whip.
Spread on cooled cake.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix like pie dough and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: best ever cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour over cake while still hot.

title: easy chicken-n-rice
directions: Mix water, rice and soup mix in baking dish.
Put chicken on top.
Place butter on top.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: broiled fish
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Arrange on greased rack of broiler pan. Brush with some of the melted butter.
Broil 4-inches from heat for 5 to 10 minutes, or until fish flakes easily when tested.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Add remaining butter and toss well. Sprinkle on fish. Broil 1 to 2 minutes or until browned. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: easy choco-nut dessert
directions: Tear cake into small pieces and layer in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Cool slightly and pour over cake; cool for half an hour in refrigerator.
In small bowl, fold into whipped topping the chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Spread mixture over top of pudding.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the lukewarm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and stir.
Melt shortening and set aside. Heat milk to lukewarm. Add salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat eggs and add to yeast.
Pour into milk. Add enough flour to make batter.
Beat until smooth. Add butter and Crisco. Stir well. Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until elastic.
Put into greased container. Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Rise and punch down 3 times. Make into rolls.
Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 350°.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze.
Serve with sweet or sour soda.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbling, approximately 1/2 hour.

title: raisin applesauce cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Add shortening, sugar, egg and applesauce.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in rolled oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons a few inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: island dreams
directions: Toast coconut and almonds on cookie sheet at 350° for 4 to 6 minutes.
Watch carefully; stir occasionally.
Cream butter and white and brown sugars until light.
Add vanilla and coconut extracts.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cornstarch.
Stir into butter mixture using a spoon rather than a mixer.
Add coconut and almonds.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing to a rack to complete cooling.

title: trini's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, and vanilla with electric mixer until creamy.
Add salt, soda, baking powder and water (*Note:
pour water directly on top of baking powder) and stir by hand.
Add flour one cup at a time and mix well by hand.
Add chocolate chips and nuts to mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mayonnaise and paprika, together. Pour into muffin tins lined with paper cups.
Freeze.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, zucchini and vanilla.
Nuts are good to add.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: double-crusted apple-cranberry pie
directions: Work the flour, salt, butter and shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle in the water a bit at a time.
Gently toss with fork to bring mixture together into a moist mass.
Chill.
Divide.
Roll.

title: german sauerbraten meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef with egg, bread crumbs, 1/4 cup water, onion and salt in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bring 1 1/2 cups water to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in bouillon cubes, brown sugar, raisins, lemon juice and gingersnap crumbs.
Add meatballs.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Turn over meatballs and baste with sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: date bread
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into a bowl and let cool.
Then mix the
remaining ingredients, then add first mixture, folding in. Bake it in a greased pan 1 hour at 350°.
Double this recipe to make 1 large and 1 small bread pan, or 2 the same size (medium pans.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind berries.
Cover with sugar and let set overnight.
Prepare Jell-O according to package and when thickened, add berries, pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into serving dish and refrigerate.

title: porcupine beef balls
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, salt, pepper and rice in bowl.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole with lid.
Combine soup and water; pour over meatballs.
Cook, covered, in a 350° oven for about 1 hour or until rice is tender when pressed lightly between fingers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Mix the jello and water until dissolved.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the sour cream.
Chill 1/2 of this mixture for 1 1/2 hours.
Leave the other 1/2 out at room temperature.
Spread refrigerated mixture with sour cream.
Chill 15 minutes.
Top with other 1/2 of mixture.
Chill 2 hours.

title: anise biscotti
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat about 3 or 4 minutes and add baking powder and flour.
Mix well.
Batter will be soft.
Place batter on ungreased sheet in row with spoon. Makes about 6 rows.
Put 2 rows on each cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: corn and potato chowder(serves 8)
directions: Place the celery, leeks and potatoes in a soup pot and sweat them in the butter over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add the stock and bay leaves.
Bring the soup to a boil, then reduce the heat to a simmer.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add the frozen corn kernels.
Cook for 3 minutes, then stir in the cream or milk and parsley and season with salt and pepper.
Add the curry powder, if desired.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: In a large, heavy pan, brown meat.
(Use shortening if necessary.)
Pour off fat.
Add soup, onion and garlic.
Cover; cook over low heat about 3 hours or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Skim off fat.
Thicken gravy, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken style seasoning
directions: Whiz in blender all ingredients except parsley flakes until very fine.
Add parsley flakes.

title: walnut pound cake
directions: Beat margarine and shortening together.
Add sugar, creaming until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350.

title: fried salmon cakes
directions: Form salmon like hamburger patties.
In skillet, add Wesson oil to cover bottom.
Fry on medium-high until brown, then turn patties over.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: microwave squash parmesan
directions: Cook onion, squash and water, covered tightly, on Full power for 7 minutes.
Drain.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except strawberries and cook until clear, two or three minutes.
Let cool.
Drain berries and place in pie shell.
Pour mixture over them.
Refrigerate for three or four hours before serving.
Top with whipped cream.
Keep refrigerated.

title: frito tacos
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and pepper plus garlic salt.
Put beef on top of corn chips and add shredded lettuce, grated cheese, chopped tomatoes, chopped onions, salsa, guacamole and sour cream.

title: garden beef stew
directions: In plastic bag, toss beef with flour and seasoned salt. In Dutch oven, brown beef
and
onions in hot oil until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until well mixed. Bring to a boil,	reduce	heat and simmer, covered, 90 minutes or until beef is tender.
Yields 9 cups stew.

title: easy white bread
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, the sugar, salt and yeast in large bowl. Heat the milk and vegetable oil to 120°.
Add egg to flour and warm liquid.
Beat until smooth.
Add 4 to 4 1/2 more cups flour; mix until a smooth dough.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Put into 2 large greased bread pans.
Let rise again, 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic cherry tomatoes
directions: Place skillet over low heat.
Add butter and melt.
Add garlic and heat, but do not brown.
Add tomatoes.
Heat for 4 minutes over very low flame.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.
(Garnish.)
Place tomatoes on a bed of watercress. Tuck sprigs of watercress among tomatoes.
Serve hot.

title: fudge sauce
directions: In a 2 cup glass measuring cup or microwavable bowl, place chocolate chips, water and butter or margarine.
Microwave, uncovered, at 100% power (700 watts) for 1 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is melted.
Remove from oven.
Stir until mixture is blended and smooth.
Stir in corn syrup and vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Cover and refrigerate leftovers.
To reheat, microwave uncovered at 100% power for 1 minute.
Stir.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Put apples in bottom of pan.
Cut bread into 3 strips.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar, beaten egg and cinnamon to taste; mix well. Lay bread over top of apples.
Pour margarine-sugar mixture over bread.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Layer meat, onion soup, cream of mushroom soup and Tater Tots. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese bread dip
directions: Cut out top from the bread and empty the bread so that only a shell is left.
Blend the rest of the ingredients and press the mixture into the bread shell.
Replace the top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: oatmeal sandwich cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla. Combine flour, cinnamon, soda, salt, and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: vegetable foil bake(for grill)
directions: Dial 411.
Ask for number of local pizzeria (one that delivers).
Call and order what you like.
Pay when they come to door (don't forget to tip).
Each pie has eight servings.

title: chow chow
directions: Sweeten to taste; cook 10 minutes.

title: stuffed peaches
directions: Save 1/4 cup pineapple juice.
Drain peaches; let set.
Drain pineapple well.
Cream the drained pineapple, cream cheese, 10x sugar and cinnamon until fluffy.
Add pineapple juice, a little at a time, if needed.
Stuff peach halves with cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon; top with a cherry.
When serving, put a paper towel on bottom of tray.
Put lettuce leaves on top of paper towels.
Place peach halves on lettuce leaves.

title: quick chili rice
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add spices, corn, green pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Cover; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Stir in rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese; serve.
Goes well with side salad with Ranch dressing and hot corn bread.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: italian cheese bread
directions: Combine all filling ingredients in a bowl and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine 1-1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and dry yeast; mix well.
In a saucepan, heat milk, water, and butter until warm, add with egg to flour mixture.
Blend until moistened.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Gradually stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Grease a 12 cup Bundt pan, sprinkle with poppy seed.
