Put 1/2 the batter into the pan.
Spread with filling.
Top with remaining batter.
Don't worry about covering the filling.
Cover let rise until doubled about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: sweet and sour baked chicken
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour.

title: layer nacho dip
directions: If you would like, you can mix the cheese.
Combine beans and taco mix.
Spread mixture evenly in a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Layer the remaining ingredients in order listed.
Serve with large tortilla chips.

title: cream cheese dessert ball(party food)
directions: Mix cream cheese and vanilla pudding with hands.
Fold in (drained) fruit cocktail.
Chill.
Form into ball and roll in pecans.
Serve with graham crackers.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding powder over the pineapple or fruit cocktail real well. Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly and chill. Keeps well.

title: lo-cal cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, pudding, jello and pineapple with spoon, not mixer.
Add maraschino cherries and Lite Cool Whip last.
Spoon into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender, drain and mash. Add all ingredients, except 1/2 margarine.
Melt remaining butter, pour mixture in baking dish.
Spread melted butter over top. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix and cook in Bundt pan.
Mix confectioners sugar and 1/2 cup walnuts for topping.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg. Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix turkey, egg and bread cubes from Stove Top.
Add bouillon cubes and seasoning packet from Stove Top to boiling water.
Stir until bouillon dissolves.
Add to turkey mixture.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: tea
directions: Boil 1 quart water and add tea bags.
Let set for 5 minutes. Mix sugar and 2 cups water and boil 5 minutes.
Combine orange, lemon and tea together.
Add sugar and water mixture to tea mixture.
Add 2 quarts tap water and serve.

title: wacky cake
directions: In bowl, sift and mix together the flour, sugar, soda, cocoa and salt.
Make 3 wells in the flour mixture.
Put 1 teaspoon of vanilla in the first, 1 teaspoon of vinegar in the second and 6 tablespoons of melted margarine in the third.
Pour 1 cup of water over all and mix with a fork until ingredients are entirely moist. Pour into a Pam sprayed 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
This makes 1 layer.

title: pantry-shelf beans
directions: Cook combined ingredients over low heat for about 2 hours, uncovered.
Stir often to avoid sticking on bottom of pan.
May be cooked in 300° oven, uncovered, about 2 hours, if preferred. Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamed meat(no. k-75)
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch pieces; grind.
Cook meat in its own fat until brown, stirring frequently.
Cook onions in bacon fat; add flour and mix thoroughly.
Mix milk and beef stock or water; heat. Add hot milk to fat and flour mixture gradually.
Heat to boiling point; boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper. Pour sauce over meat; simmer until meat is well done, but not overcooked.
Serve on toast.
Yields 100 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a saucepan combine salt, vinegar, caraway seeds and sugar. Bring to boil over medium heat. Stir in sauerkraut, onion, celery, pepper & pimento. Remove from heat & let marinate overnight before serving. This stores well for later use.

title: large shellroni and sausage
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Add green pepper and onion. Cook until tender.
Stir in broken tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add sugar, salt and chili powder. Stir, cover and simmer 45 minutes. Cook shellroni
and drain well. Add to sauce. Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.

title: baked brie spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set Brie in ovenproof dish.
Spread butter over top.
Arrange sliced almonds on butter.
Bake until softened and heated through, 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm with breads, apples, etc.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add other ingredients and simmer.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla in a large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in flour.
Stir in 3/4 cup morsels.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle with remaining morsels.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Spread.
Sprinkle colored sugar over melted chocolate. Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: sticks for kids
directions: Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar to sweet cream. Stir in graham flour until very thick.
Shape into sticks with hands.
Bake slowly for 2 or 3 hours in a 250° oven.
Great for cutting teeth.

title: dilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir until dissolved.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm.
In large mixing bowl, combine cottage cheese, sugar, minced onion, melted oleo, dill seed, salt, soda and eggs.
Blend well.
Add yeast mixture.
Gradually add 5 cups flour and mix well.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and no longer sticky.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease all sides.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap.
Let rise until doubled in size, approximately 1 hour.
Punch down.
Divide into 3 portions; form into loaves.
Place in 3 greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Cover with a towel and let rise again until tops of loaves are even or slightly above edge of pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
Brush with melted oleo.
This bread is excellent toasted.
It enhances the flavor.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Stir in pineapple. Sift flour, soda, salt and nutmeg together.
Stir into the sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and put on a greased cookie sheet by spoonfuls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: double good texas peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a 1 1/2-quart pan. Fold in the peanut butter and shortening and melt again.
Stir in peanuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Chill. Store in refrigerator.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine apples, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Put into a buttered pie tin and place in oven while preparing rest of ingredients.
Cream the butter, add the remaining 1/2 cup sugar, egg and flour mixed with the baking powder and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Drop and spread over top of apple mixture in oven and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. May be served with whipped cream, plain milk or ice cream.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all wet ingredients with baking powder first.
Then mix in flour, sugar and salt.
Using a small ice cream scoop, fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: whole wheat chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix liquids.
Add to dry ingredients, beating.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spud burgers
directions: Mix and make into patties and grill or fry.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions and celery in water 10 to 15 minutes. Add milk and butter.
Mix flour and egg together.
Drop by teaspoon.
Cook 10 more minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain excess grease. Add mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, canned tomatoes (or fresh ones) and taco seasoning.
Stir well and simmer.
Line bottom of baking pan with nacho chips.
Pour 1/2 of meat mixture over chips. Cover with another layer of chips and add remaining meat mixture. Sprinkle grated cheese over final layer.
Place in 325° oven just long enough to melt cheese.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Mix sugars and butter together.
Beat in eggs, vanilla, flour and pecans. Pour into 9-inch pie crust and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bread custard pudding
directions: Cut crust from bread; butter one side.
Combine eggs, sugar and flavorings; add milk slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves. Put into baking dish, buttered side up.
Place in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease. Mix ingredients and cook over medium heat. Stir occasionally. Cook 1 hour.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Mix late in afternoon.
Knead down throughout the evening. Mold into rolls before going to bed.
Cover well.
Let rise overnight.
Bake in the morning at 375° until done.

title: peanut butter patties
directions: Slice sugar cookie dough, then cut slices in half.
Shape dough to fit tiny muffin pans.
Bake as directed on cookie package.
As soon as taken out of oven, immediately press peanut butter cup into center of each cookie shell.

title: boiler maker barbecue sauce
directions: In a non-reactive saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and cook slowly until translucent. Add garlic, chili powder and jalapeno and cook until fragrant. Add beer, bourbon, vinegar and sugar and cook until reduced by half, 5 to 10 minutes. Add the rest of the ingredients. Stir well and simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Sauce can be stored in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks. Makes 3 cups.

title: peanut butter-chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk. Heat over medium stove until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boil.
Cook until soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: easy molasses cookies
directions: To beaten egg, add sugar, shortening and molasses; beat well. Sift together dry ingredients and combine with egg mixture.
Beat well.
Drop by teaspoon into bowl of granulated sugar and roll to coat.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: candy coating for quick cake
directions: Arrange chocolate covered mints in a single layer over top of hot cake.
Put in oven long enough to melt candy.
Remove from the oven; smooth with a spatula to make a marble effect.
Serve.

title: annette's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs, baking powder, and flavoring.
Add flour and milk, alternating.
Stir in coconut.
Bake in greased and floured 10 inch bundt or tube pan at 325 degrees for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on wire rack. This can also be baked in small loaf pans which have been greased and coated with additional coconut.
These can be baked and wrapped in foil or plastic wrap for gifts.
They freeze well.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Make roux with butter and flour.
Saute carrots in butter while making roux.
Pour roux and carrots in a large pot on medium heat. Add 2 quarts of whipping cream one at a time, stirring continuously.
Add half and half.
Stir in crabmeat and continue stirring until smooth and creamy.
Add Rose and stir.
Serve.

title: chuck's caesar salad dressing
directions: Use blender.
Blend all ingredients in blender until dressing consistency.
Use over fresh romaine lettuce
and croutons. Sprinkle salad with Parmesan cheese.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix first
ingredients
together.
Preheat
oven
to 350°. Combine all
ingredients
and
shape into 1-inch balls. Place meat balls in
a roasting pan or crock-pot and add gravy or sauce and serve with hot butter noodles or other pasta.

title: kolackies
directions: Mix together the oleo, flour and ice cream and let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Roll out on floured surface and cut into 2 to 3-inch squares.
Put 1 teaspoon preserves in middle. Fold corners up to center.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for approximately 14 to 15 minutes until slightly brown on bottoms. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when done.
Do not bake until brown on top; they will look not quite done.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with the cheese slices.
Combine soup and lemon juice. Stir well and spoon evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle with the stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: manicotti
directions: Spoon enough sauce to cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Rinse spinach under running cold water to separate; drain. Place spinach on towels and squeeze until dry.
Mix everything together, except sauce and shells.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients except carrots and potatoes; simmer 1 hour.
Add remaining vegetables and simmer another 20 minutes.
(A quart of whole tomatoes can be substituted for tomato soup and sauce.)

title: trivia roll
directions: Spread dough on greased cookie sheet.
Down center spread pepper salad.
Layer cheese and salami.
Roll into log shape. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: greaseless pork chops
directions: Saute number of pork chops desired until nicely browned.
Mix water, vinegar and seasonings.
Pour liquid over meat; continue cooking until chops are adequately cooked.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Blend cheese, pudding and milk until thick and smooth.
Fill pie crust. Top with pie filling, fruit or berries.

title: mama's quiche(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg with whisk; blend in flour and beat in mayo.
Add milk and blend well.
Fold in cheese and onion. Fill pie shell and bake for 45 minutes.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: About 20 minutes before serving:
In 10-inch skillet over medium-low heat, in hot oil, stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover pan and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve immediately.
(Vegetables will be crisp.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar and set aside.
Mix together margarine and pretzels and press into the bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
While still warm, spread the cheese mixture over pretzel crust.
Sprinkle with coconut; cool, then spread with Cool Whip.
Mix jello with hot water.
Add nectar and pineapple.
Chill until it begins to congeal and pour over Cool Whip layer.

title: pork pie
directions: Cook ground pork until done with onion and seasonings.
Boil potato, mash and mix with pork mixture (drained).
Season to taste.
Put in pie crusts.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.

title: grammie angel pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add baking powder and sugar.
Beat again until stiff.
Add crumbs and pecans.
Add vanilla.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together; roll into balls. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar-free lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water (I add 1/2 envelope gelatin dissolved in a little water).
When cool and starts to thicken put milk
in
blender
with Philadelphia cream cheese. Blend well.
Add to thickened Jell-O.
Add pineapple.
You may add sliced banana (optional).
Pour
into
bowl
or
long pan. Sprinkle with chopped nuts if you desire.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat together egg and water.
Mix together crumbs and cheese. Dip chicken breasts in egg and water.
Roll in bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese mixture.
Brown in hot oil.
Place in baking dish. Pour tomato sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle on some oregano, then the Mozzarella cheese.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sour cream.
Stir in taco seasoning package.
Refrigerate.
Add 1 jar salsa.
Cut up tomatoes, green peppers and black olives. Layer on top of each other. Serve with taco chips.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add onion and margarine.
Mix rice, water and soup and Cheez Whiz.
Combine all ingredients together; put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done; pinch into pieces.
Pour rice (uncooked) into your dish; add all soups and chicken broth.
Add parsley.
Put a little butter on top in several places.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until golden brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together egg, sugar and shortening.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cassata
directions: Slice cake into 4 layers.
Reserve a layer for top.
Drizzle orange liqueur over remaining 3 layers.
Combine cheese, sugar, almond extract, chocolate and fruit.
Use as a filling for cake layers.
Top with pain layer.
Chill.
Heat chocolate with coffee in a heavy saucepan until chocolate is melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, piece by piece, beating until frosting is smooth.
Chill until of spreading consistency.
Spread frosting over sides and top of cake.
Swirl, as desired.
Decorate with whipped cream rosettes.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes 1 cake.

title: fresh baked ham
directions: Cook until thick.
Cook ham for 30 minutes per pound, wrapped in foil, fat side up.
Leave skin on until last 45 minutes. Remove skin.
Score fat and stick cloves in.
Apply pineapple and glaze; cook the other 45 minutes.
If you want it to be a little more brown, leave unwrapped a few minutes before taking out of oven.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Sift the flour with the baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Cream the butter and sugar thoroughly in a large mixing bowl.
Beat in egg.
Stir in milk, lemon juice, pineapple with its syrup and nuts.
Add flour mixture all at once and stir just until dry ingredients are dampened.
Turn into a well-greased loaf pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven until done when tested (about 55 minutes).
Let cool in pan 5 minutes, then turn out on cooling rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: ripe cucumber pickles
directions: Pare and slice cukes lengthwise; remove seeds.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand 24 hours.
Place the salted cukes in a colander or on a thin cloth tied over the top of a pan; drain 1 hour.
Boil sugar, spices and vinegar 5 minutes; add cukes. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal immediately.

title: barbecue ham sandwiches
directions: Bring all ingredients, except ham, to a boil; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add the chipped ham and cook an additional 20 minutes. Serve on hamburg buns.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook potatoes until done. Peel and cream. Add sugar and vanilla. Mix well until thick enough to roll out. Roll out as for pastry for pie. Spread peanut butter and roll it up; slice crosswise with a thread.

title: pineapple pecan pie
directions: Mix pineapple and butter pecan pie filling together.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Put all in a bowl and mix at medium speed 5 minutes.
Pour in an angel food pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: succulent chicken wings
directions: Cut wings apart at both joints (save tips for soup stock). In large bowl, combine wings with other ingredients and marinate overnight.
Drain and save marinade.
Heat oven to 450°.
Arrange wings on rack in roasting pan.
Roast 35 to 45 minutes or until crisp.
Spoon marinade over wings several times while cooking.

title: quick parmesan potatoes
directions: Place butter in small bowl and microwave until just melted. In separate bowl, mix cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and dip cut side into melted butter, then into cheese mixture.
Place potatoes,
cut side up, in 1-quart microwave dish or in 8-inch round pie plate.
Microwave on High 7 to 10 minutes, until potatoes are fork-tender.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter parfait
directions: Combine all ingredients; spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: candied kielbasi
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours on stove or 4 hours in crock-pot.

title: tortilla appetizer
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together until well blended.
Spread mixture on tortillas, alternating tortillas and mixture.
It will make 3 stacks of 4 tortillas each.
Keep in refrigerator.
Cut like a pizza.
Dip slices into taco sauce or spread taco sauce on top before serving.

title: northern bean bake
directions: Place hamburger meat in skillet with onion and bell pepper. Cook until brown.
Hard fry bacon; crush bacon in small pieces. Drain grease off meat.
Place in 3-quart casserole dish or crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chuck roast
directions: Brown meat in greased skillet after dredging with flour, salt and pepper.
Place browned meat in pot for oven.
Top with onion slices and 1 tablespoon catsup.
Bake 1/2 hour covered.
Take onion off and, after turning, replace onion on top.
Put other tablespoon catsup on top.
Cover with lid or foil.
Cook until tender at 300°, turning often.

title: paneed (breaded) meat
directions: Salt and pepper your choice of meat.
Dip in egg wash.
Dust with bread crumbs and fry.

title: marinated coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage, slice red onion (separate), slice bell pepper. Layer cabbage, onion, and bell pepper. Sprinkle top with sugar. Spread celery seed over sugar. Combine vinegar, vegetable oil, and dry mustard. Bring to a boil and pour over cabbage, onion, and bell pepper. Refrigerate over night.

title: 8 minute cheesecake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fruit, if desired.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients together and frost.

title: parm-a-meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except barbecue sauce.
Mix lightly.
In a 10 x 6-inch baking dish, shape into a loaf.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Spread on sauce.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Sprinkle on additional cheese.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix the oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Add remaining ingredients; mix well and add 1 cup raisins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: In food processor, combine sugar and egg; process for 1 minute.
Add butter and vanilla; process for 1 minute.
Add flour; process for 20 seconds, until flour is mixed.
Add walnuts and pulse.
Do not over process.
Roll dough into 3 cylinders, 1 1/2 to 2 inches wide.
Chill for about 1 hour, then slice into 1/4-inch thick pieces.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: low sodium vegetable and ham soup
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add onion. Saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and 5 cups water. Bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to simmer. Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until potato is tender. Garnish with carrot curls and fresh chives, if desired.

title: honey q baked beans
directions: Use regular size baking dish.
Put beans in dish, then add cut up onion or use long strips.
Then add brown sugar, white sugar and barbecue sauce.
Stir all together, then put in oven for 35 minutes at 375° or until turns brown.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix everything but chicken together.
Put chicken in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Pour cranberry mixture over chicken.
Cover and chill at least overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Save 1/4 cup for garnish.
Mix jello with boiling water; let cool.
Cream sugar with cream cheese, then mix jello, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add crushed pineapple.
Pour gently over graham crackers. Garnish with graham crackers, chopped walnuts and maraschino cherries.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip brownies
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla and stir. Add dry ingredients, stir in chocolate chips. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs in bowl. Heat 1-inch of oil in skillet over medium heat. Pour batter in funnel. Hold your finger over end of funnel. Drizzle spiral shapes into oil. Cook until brown on both sides. Drain on a paper towel. Coat with confectioners sugar.

title: cookies and candy
directions: Cream Crisco, butter, white and brown sugar together.
Add egg, flour, water, soda and salt.
Add vanilla.
Add 1/2 cup M&M's (chopped) to dough.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Place M&M's on dough.
Bake in oven at 325° for 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into 9 inch unbaked pastry shell (deep).
Bake in oven at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: kathy's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, melt 1 cup butter.
Stir in cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
In a large mixing bowl combine flour, brown sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa mixture; beat well.
Stir in 1/3 cup of Eagle Brand milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Roll into little balls and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. When baked, roll in powdered sugar.

title: rhubarb dumplings
directions: Put flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cut butter into dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, mix well.
Roll dough out to about 1/4-inch thickness, then spread it with butter, sugar and rhubarb, which has been chopped into 1/4-inch slices and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Roll dough up in jelly roll fashion, cut into slices 1 1/2 to 2 inches thick.
Lay slices flat into a baking dish and pour Sweet Sauce over.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: familia
directions: Mix together and store in covered bowl in refrigerator.
Eat raw with milk for cereal or as snack.
(This is an excellent snack food for trips as you can add instant milk and water and have a good, nourishing meal.)

title: indoor barbecued alligator(seminole style)
directions: Mix liquid
smoke,
juices,
water
and
Worcestershire sauce. Add meat and
let	stand
in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours, up to 48
hours won't hurt.
Keep covered and turn meat often during the
day.
Remove meat from marinade and place in a shallow, oiled baking
pan.
Place
in
a	preheated oven at 300° for 2 hours, basting
with melted butter to which some of the marinade has been added.
Lower heat to 275° and continue baking until tender.

title: ham spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Cover and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken rosemary
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and paprika. Place in baking dish. Dot with margarine. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 25 minutes. Add wine, bouillon cube and rosemary. Continue to cook, basting chicken frequently, until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. In a seperate bowl beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored; blend into creamed mixture. Sift together cake flour, baking powder, and salt. Resift 3 times, so it will be mixed well. Beat all ingredients until well mixed. Bake in greased bundt pan for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: rice krispies meringues
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar gradually, beating until mixture is like meringue.
Add extract and mix.
Stir in Rice Krispies and chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on 2 ungreased cookie sheets.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place 1-inch of water in large pan.
Add potatoes, onion, parsley and 2 teaspoons salt.
Bring to boil, covered.
Cook just until slightly tender, about 5 minutes from time of boil.
Drain.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding corn bread last. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes. Serve while hot. Serves 12.

title: layered lemon jello salad
directions: You will need an 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch dish for this recipe.

title: joshua's cheese and macaroni
directions: Make macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Add grated cheese and milk.
Stir until well mixed and serve.

title: um bido (greens and peanuts)
directions: Cook spinach in enough boiling water to cover.
Frozen spinach should be cooked in 1/2 cup water or less.
Cook for 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle in peanuts and stir well.
Continue cooking over medium heat for about 30 minutes, adding more water if necessary to prevent burning.
Just before serving, drain and mix in butter, salt and pepper.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain sweet potatoes; warm on top of stove.
Add English walnuts, coconut and brown sugar.
Spread in pan.
Cover with small marshmallows.
Brown in oven.

title: mayo salad
directions: Mix mayo and milk in empty jar.
Shake well.
Pour over lettuce and tomato salad.

title: minestrone
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot, except zucchini.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 16 hours (high for 4 to 6 hours).
During last hour, remove meat and bones.
Cut meat from bones and return to soup with zucchini.
Turn crock-pot to high; cook 1 hour.
Ladle into bowls; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve with crusty French bread.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saut onions in butter; add soups alternately with half and half. Add corn and clams. Cook on low to medium on top of stove for 1 hour or in crock-pot on high for 1 hour.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and butter or margarine to a boil.
All at once, pour in flour, stirring rapidly.
Cook until thickens and leaves side of pan.
Remove from heat and add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition until mixture looks satiny.
Drop 1 teaspoon of mixture one-inch apart on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 450° until they brown a little.

title: almond tea
directions: Steep boiling water and tea bag for 10 minutes.
Boil 4 cups water and sugar for seven minutes; add to tea.
Combine lemon juice and extracts, add to tea mixture.

title: red punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Makes approximately 2 gallons.

title: creole black-eyed peas
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute onion, green pepper and celery in drippings until tender. Stir in Ro-Tel, peas, sugar, salt to taste, bay leaf and half the crumbled bacon.
Cook over low heat 30 to 45 minutes.
Add water if necessary.
Remove bay leaf and sprinkle with remaining crumbled bacon just before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: asparagus and peas
directions: Place asparagus in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix peas with mushroom soup and spread over asparagus.
Add salt and pepper, then add chopped water chestnuts and grated cheese.
Cut bread into four finger-length pieces, coating each slice in melted oleo and arrange over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and turn into a greased 9 x 11 casserole. Top with 1 pack of coarse cracker crumbs tossed in 1/2 stick of melted butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: quicky cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls in powdered sugar and roll in a ball.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chrusciki(polish love knots)
directions: Beat egg yolks until stiff.
Add milk, pinch of salt, whiskey and sugar.
Blend flour and knead until smooth.
Refrigerate dough for at least 1 hour or even overnight.
Cut dough into 4 pieces, working 1 at a time.
Refrigerate rest.
Roll very thin and cut into strips about 4 x 2-inches with slanted edges.
Make a 1-inch slit in center of each.
Draw 1 end through slit and curl back in opposite direction.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water with celery tops until tender. Cool, debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Mix onion, soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes together.
Have ready the tortillas, grated cheese, garlic salt and chili powder.

title: spinach-rice enchiladas
directions: Place water and onion in a medium saucepan.
Saute until onion softens slightly.
Add spinach.
Cover and steam until just tender (4 to 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add rice and seasonings. Mix and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 cup of sauce over the bottom of a casserole dish.
Spread a line of the spinach-rice mix down the center of a tortilla.
Roll up and place, seam side down in casserole dish.
Repeat until all of the ingredients are used.
Pour the remaining sauce over the tortillas.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: smothered potatoes
directions: Heat fat in heavy frying pan.
Add potatoes, water, salt, paprika, onions and mango.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add milk.
Cover and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take meat from chicken.
Place in a 13 1/2 x 9-inch greased casserole dish.
Mix soups; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over top.
Mix broth and margarine together.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 325° until hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in a 3-quart casserole (or 9 x 9-inch). Mix soups and milk together, then pour over chicken.

title: yellow coconut cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed.
Make coconut pudding as directed. Add cream cheese to pudding mixture.
When cake is cool, ice with pudding and cream cheese mixture.
Spread container of Cool Whip over pudding and cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut and serve.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream cheese with butter.
Gradually blend in flour and seasonings.
Use cookie press to make cheese straws or roll out like pie crust and cut in thin strips.
(One teaspoon of hot water may be added if dough is too stiff.)
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with salt while still in pan.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: crunch cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at one time; beat 12 minutes.
Place in a tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well. Chill and serve.

title: potato snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice unpeeled potatoes about 1/4 inch thick or in wedges.
Place in single layer on a nonstick cookie sheet for 30 to 40 minutes.
Adjust length of baking time according to shape of potato cut and thickness of slices.
Salt to taste.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in an 8-inch square greased and floured pan. Blend ingredients until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: frozen chocolate dessert
directions: Combine first three ingredients in double boiler; cook on low until chocolate and marshmallows melt.
Remove from heat and cool. Combine margarine and coconut over medium heat until coconut is light brown.
Remove from heat and add graham cracker crumbs. Press 3/4 crumb mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut ice cream into
1/2-inch slices and use half on crumb mixture.
Pour half chocolate mixture over ice cream and repeat layers.
Combine remaining crumbs and nuts; sprinkle on top.
Freeze until firm.

title: banana coconut loaf
directions: Break eggs in a mixing bowl.
Beat until light and frothy.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Beat well.
Stir in mashed banana and flavoring.
In another bowl, measure in remaining ingredients. Stir until well mixed.
Pour over batter.
Stir just to combine. Spoon into greased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool and wrap.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl; microwave for 3 minutes. Repeat this 2 more times.
Stir about 4 to 5 minutes.
Drop on foil by spoon fulls.
If hardens before you finish dropping add tablespoon of water and they will soften enough to let you finish dropping.

title: cheese dip in french bread
directions: Mix all together and fill inside of French loaf.
Fill with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chicken and dorito casserole
directions: After chicken is deboned, put on top of Doritos in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix onion, soup, broth and pepper in bowl.
Pour over meat and Doritos.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: butterscotch chewy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs with beater in top of a double boiler.
Blend in brown sugar and butter.
Place over boiling water, stirring constantly until hot, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix together flour and baking powder.
Add all at once to other mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook white sugar, water and Karo until threads spins (230° soft ball).
Add raw peanuts and stir continuously after peanuts are added.
Cook until it turns a brownish gold.
Take from fire (300° hard crack).

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic, green pepper, oregano, chili powder and beef together.
Drain fat, if any.
Then add 7 to 8 cups water, depending on desired thickness.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bring mixture to a boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Can top with Cheddar cheese, grated.
Serve with cornbread.

title: tavern from iowa(sloppy joes)
directions: Boil onion in water until tender.
Add other ingredients and cook down.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: warmed smoked beef dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except nuts.
Sprinkle nuts on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes at the most.

title: strawberry spritzer
directions: Blend 2 packages of room temperature strawberries until smooth. Combine strawberries, grape juice and remaining strawberries (undrained) in punch bowl.
Add carbonated water or ginger ale slowly.
Makes 24 (4 ounce) servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook, debone and cube chicken.
Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add soups, broth, chicken and rice.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs, cheese and ripe olives.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, carrots and vanilla; beat until combined.
Stir in pineapple and nuts. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: norwegian apple bake
directions: Put the eggs into a large bowl, add 1 cup of the sugar, and beat until stiff and creamy.
Put the butter and milk into a sauce pan and heat gently until the butter has melted.
Meanwhile, arrange the apple slices in a shallow ovenproof dish 12 inches diameter, buttered.

title: lobster crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine seafood with veggies.
Stir in mayonnaise and seasonings.
Pour mixture into greased casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: easy shrimp
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in margarine.
Add all spices.
Add shrimp and saute until done.
Add mushroom soup and water chestnuts.
Serve over rice.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and chill.
When ready to serve, add chilled ginger ale.
Serve over a big chunk of ice. Serves 50.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into chilled, unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until brown, for about 50 minutes.
Use 3 eggs, more nuts, raisins and coconut for a larger pie.

title: easy chicken 'n rice
directions: Slice margarine in baking dish.
Sprinkle in rice.
Arrange chicken on top of rice.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt margarine. Stir in crumbs. Pat mixture firmly into pan.

title: ritz cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers and stir in melted butter.
Put mixture in bottom of pan.
Save some of the mixture to sprinkle on top.
Cook pineapple and sugar.
Add egg yolks and cook until thick.
Remove off heat and add 1 small box lemon jello in the mixture and stir well.
Let cool.
Beat the egg whites until stiff with 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold into cooked mixture.
Then pour over Ritz cracker crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle rest of cracker crumbs on top.
Let cool before serving.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mash cranberry sauce, add lemon juice and blend. Pour into 1 quart refrigerator tray or loaf pan. Soften cream cheese, add sugar and mayonnaise and mix well. Add nuts, fold in Cool Whip. Spoon cheese mixture over cranberry mixture. Freeze until firm.

title: low calorie green bean salad
directions: Mix beans, onion and green pepper together. Combine the other ingredients and boil.
Pour over vegetables. Chill.
Recipe can be halved.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in buttered pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
Mix flour, sugar and butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tangy sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients in skillet with beef and onions.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on buns or bread.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until straw comes out clean.

title: cheesy chicken enchilada bake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheese, lettuce and sour cream). Bring to a boil in saucepan.
When bubbly, transfer to a casserole dish and top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.
Serve in tortillas (see package for heating instructions) and add lettuce.
Fold tortillas, sprinkle with shredded cheese, then melt it.
Add sour cream.

title: oriental pork chops
directions: Dice pork chops and saute in shortening.
Drain fat.
Set meat aside.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flour and flavoring. Don't overbeat.
Put in greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken prosciutto
directions: Pound chicken breast with mallet until evenly flat. Place cheese and ham on the flattened chicken and roll chicken. Melt butter in saute pan. Lightly dust chicken in flour. Saute chicken, seam-side down, four minutes on each side until brown. Drain butter. Remove chicken. Deglaze pan with wine. Reduce wine by half. Add the chicken breasts back to pan, heavy cream and soy sauce. Sprinkle with Romano. Garnish with parsley. Serve with mashed potatoes, fettuccine Alfredo or baked potatoes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Combine biscuit mix and Sourdough Starter, stirring until biscuit mix is moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 3 to 4 times.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup crumbs on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Position knife blade in food procesor bowl.
Add cream cheese and next five ingredients. Process until smooth.
Add egg substitute and process just until blended.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes or until center is almost set.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup remaining crumbs.
Cool completely.

title: pasta sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan and simmer for 1/2 hour. Pour on any of your favorite pasta dishes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients and cook until simmering and butter is melted.
Stir well.
Baste on chicken on grill after it is almost done.
Butter in sauce will cause it to burn if left on grill too long.
Yields 1/2 gallon sauce.

title: barbecue
directions: Add all together and simmer 20 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: In a large skillet, fry hamburg.
When done, remove from pan and drain any fat with paper towel.
Simmer onion, bell pepper and margarine until tender.
Add cooked hamburg, tomato soup, beans, vinegar, pepper and chili powder; stir well.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet abundance bread pudding
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a 3-quart rectangular baking dish, layer 1/2 of the bread cubes, raisins, coconut and pecans. Repeat the layers; set aside.
In a large bowl, stir together the beaten eggs, granulated sugar, half and half or light cream, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour the milk mixture evenly over the ingredients in the baking dish.
Dot with the butter or margarine.
Bake the pudding in the 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except boiling water; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch cake pan that has been greased and lightly floured.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Top with Super Fudge Sauce (recipe following).

title: beck chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Work all ingredients together by hand and form in small balls (1 1/2-inches in diameter).
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar and crushed pretzels.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Put in freezer until completely cooled.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in jackets until firm.
Peel and cut into slices.
Put one layer of potatoes into buttered casserole and cover with 1/2 of brown sugar and dot with 1/2 of butter.
Repeat. Pour bourbon over all and bake about 30 to 45 minutes at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and roll in ground nuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour or 2.
Very good on crackers.

title: low fat fruit dip
directions: Mix well, chill and serve with fruit.

title: seafood soup(serves 6)
directions: Melt butter, turn flame off.
Add flour to butter and stir. Add cold milk and stir in.
Turn flame on low and cook until thick, medium to medium-low heat.

title: autumn harvest casserole
directions: Sprinkle turnip with salt; set aside for 30 minutes. Melt 3 tablespoons butter. Saute butter and bread crumbs; set aside. Squeeze water from turnip. Combine with carrots. Melt 4 tablespoons butter and add turnip, carrots and sugar. Turn heat low, cover and cook for 10 minutes. Uncover and stir in dill, salt and pepper to taste. Put in covered casserole. Pour on cream. Top with crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: honey baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325° for 15 minutes.
Set the ham on a rack in a roasting pan.
Roast uncovered for 45 minutes to an hour. Meanwhile, mix honey with the mustard.
Fifteen minutes before the ham is due to come out of the oven, brush the glaze over the ham and continue to bake until done.
Remove the ham from the oven and let it rest for 15 minutes before carving.
Season each slice with ground pepper.

title: orton pollock's big time meat loaf
directions: Combine this in a large bowl.
Mix lightly with hands.
Place in a bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: ribbon torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two round cake pans. Combine dry cake mix, eggs, oil and water in large mixing bowl. Mix as directed on package, but do not add contents of small packet.
Turn half of batter (about 2 1/2 cups) into one pan. Blend contents of small packet into remaining batter and turn into remaining pan.
Bake and cool as directed on package.

title: rio grande supper
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and green pepper.
Stir in corn, Cheez Whiz, barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Simmer 20 minutes. Top with corn chips.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Combine the Jell-O with the boiling water. Stir until clear. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into compote or mold and chill until firm.

title: pasta e fagioli(pasta and beans)
directions: Place beans in a large pot or bowl and add enough cold water to cover beans.
Soak beans overnight.
Drain.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and bake it at 350° for 1 hour in pan or skillet.

title: fish stock
directions: Cut
up fish, if necessary, to fit in a large saucepan. Add the
onion, celery, parsley, lemon, salt, peppercorns and cloves. Add
cups
cold	water.	Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Strain through sieve lined with
1	or 2 layers of cheesecloth.
Reserve fish for another use; discard skin, bones and seasonings.
Makes 4 cups.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Lightly saute garlic, onion and broccoli.
Meanwhile, mix eggs, milk and cheese, then add seasonings.
Mix in veggies and pour into an oiled casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ugly duckling
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and put in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: easy bean burritos
directions: Place 9 x 13-inch casserole dish beside cutting board.
Lay tortilla on cutting board and spread layer of refried beans on top.
In a line near middle of tortilla, sprinkle black olives, cheese and salsa.
Roll up tortilla and place in dish.
Repeat for remaining 9 tortillas.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or cook in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve on plates with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream on top.

title: coconut pie a la doris
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter, coconut, milk and vanilla. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add 1 can of pumpkin and soda dissolved in water, then add flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, frost with buttercream frosting.

title: cheesy rice and broccoli
directions: Combine meat, broccoli, cheese, rice, oleo, soup and milk together in a 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: beef-vegetable soup
directions: Combine meat, water, salt and pepper in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until meat can be easily removed from bones.
Remove bones, skim off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 35 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: swiss cheese mushroom pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add onions.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add fresh mushrooms, salt, Worcestershire sauce and lemon.
Cook 5 minutes. Drain.
Combine mushroom mixture and shredded cheese.
Put in unbaked shell. Add strips of pie crust across top.
Brush with egg mixed with water.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: cheddar dip
directions: Place first 5 ingredients and 1/4 cup sour cream in a bowl and beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Fold in remaining sour cream.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Stir before serving.
Makes 2 cups.

title: society pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers well.
Cover with boiling water.
Cover and let set for 24 hours.
Drain and pour fresh boiling water over cucumbers for 4 days.
On 5th day drain and slice cucumbers in 3/4-inch slices.
Cover with hot syrup made with the remaining ingredients.
Put spices in bag.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes with all 6 ingredients.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 400° oven about 30 minutes or until golden and puffy.
Can also add coconut, if desired.

title: beef jerky marinade
directions: Pour all ingredients over beef.
Let set overnight. Put on baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: baked sweet potatoes with apples
directions: Peel and pare the apples and fry them in butter until light brown.
Slice the potatoes.
Arrange the apples and potatoes in alternate layers in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt. Pour the syrup over the dish and dot with more butter.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 35 minutes.
You may crumble corn flakes over the top before you bake it or you may put a layer of marshmallows on top.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: imitation crabmeat quiche
directions: Bake crust.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour into crust. Cover exposed crust with foil before baking.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4.

title: baked squash
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain and combine all ingredients except the stuffing mix and margarine.
Melt margarine and add to stuffing mix.
Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of baking dish, cover with the squash mixture and top with the remaining stuffing mixture.
Salt and pepper squash to taste while squash is boiling. Bake at least 45 minutes at 350° or long enough for carrots to cook.

title: zucchini tomato casserole(from canadian living magazine, september, 1984)
directions: Combine cheeses, herbs, garlic, salt and pepper.
Thinly slice zucchini and tomatoes into bowls.
Butter an 8 or 9 x 2-inch square pan.
Arrange 1/2 zucchini slices in pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 cheese mix over.
Then arrange 1/2 tomato slice and 1/4 cheese over tomatoes, then arrange remaining zucchini and again, 1/4 of cheese mix.
Top with remaining tomato slices and last of cheese mix.

title: crab puffs
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Stir a little of the sauce into the egg yolk.
Add the remaining sauce, stirring constantly.
Add paprika and crab meat.
Whip the cream. Fold in egg white and whipped cream.
Place in 6 well-greased individual 20 ounce casseroles.
Place casseroles in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until puffs are firm in the center.
Serves 6.

title: apricot poppy seed muffins
directions: Empty baby food in a small bowl.
Add soda.
Stir mixture.
It will be foamy.
Set aside.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut into 1 to 2-inch cubes.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix soup, lemon juice, curry powder and mayonnaise.
Layer chicken and broccoli in buttered casserole.
Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli. Cover with cheese.
Top with bread cubes.
Bake at 325° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, beating well until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Add flour 1/2 cup at a time until well mixed.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put biscuits, sugar and cinnamon in a bag and shake.
Put in an angel food cake pan.
Bring to boil the brown sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Pecans can be placed around in layers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; mix flour, shortening, sausage and cheese.
Add milk and stir until mixture pulls away from sides of bowl.
Put mixture on lightly floured board.
Knead 30 seconds. Form bite size balls; place on a baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Cut cabbage into bite size pieces.
Mix oil, cider vinegar, sugar and seasoning packet from soup package.
Roast almond slivers and sesame seed on flat cookie sheet in 350° oven until seeds pop. Mix cabbage, Ramen noodles from package and dressing.
Pour almond slivers and sesame seed on top and then toss.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken, water, salt and sage (to taste) in a 6-quart Dutch oven.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth (save the broth); debone chicken and let cool.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to boil.
Boil for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add the final 3 ingredients.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Let dry and eat!

title: good italian dressing
directions: Use measurements on Good Seasons cruet for vinegar, oil and water.
Shake good and enjoy!

title: ham-it-up crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place ham slices on rectangles. Spread with mustard, then sprinkle with cheese.
Starting at shortest side, roll up each rectangle; press edges to seal.
Coat rolls with sesame seed (optional).
Cut each roll into 8 slices, forming 32 slices.
Place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
May be made ahead. Refrigerate whole rolls in airtight container until ready to slice and bake.

title: strawberry and onion salad
directions: Salad:
Mix lettuce, strawberries and red onion together.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into creamed mix. Add walnuts. Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares while warm. Leave in pan until cooled.

title: honey carrots
directions: Cook carrots about 10 minutes or until tender.
Use skillet, melt margarine.
Add sugar, honey and carrots.
Cook on low heat, turning until carrots are well glazed.
Serves 6.

title: easy spanish rice
directions: In saucepan combine all ingredients.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Dip green tomato slices in egg, then coat with cracker crumbs. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Turning so both sides are crispy.

title: impossible mexican quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie pan. Brown and drain beef and onion.
Stir in taco seasoning.
Sprinkle layer of peppers and cheese.
Blend rest of the ingredients and pour over top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Measure meal.
Add cooking oil and eggs; mix well.
Add sour cream and corn; mix well.
Spray 12-cup muffin pan.
Cook at 400° until brown.

title: puffy fried shrimp
directions: Fold flour, water, shortening, salt and pepper into egg whites.
Dip shrimp in mixture and fry in deep hot oil until golden.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350. When done cut into squares. Good cold or hot.

title: ham and cream cheese party ball
directions: Dice ham, saving a little to garnish ball.
Dice onions.
Mix softened cream cheese, ham, onions, Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Garnish with ham.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour.
Cook 2 minutes and gradually add broth, water, milk and salt.
Cook until thickened.
Add eggs to hot mixture.
Stir in cubed chicken.
Cover a baking dish with Stove Top and pour hot mixture over Stove Top.
Crumble 2 slices of toast over the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: moist banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix with onion, sour cream, mushroom soup and carrots.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Put half of stuffing on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour mixture on top of stuffing and use the rest of stuffing on top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hungarian goulash soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook bacon until almost crisp.
Add green pepper, onions and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add beef cubes and brown on all sides.
Sprinkle with seasonings; stir and cook for 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
About 1/2 hour before serving, add potatoes and cook until tender.

title: fruit ices
directions: You will need popsicle molds or small cups and lollipop sticks.
Push the lollipop sticks halfway in the mold or stand them up in small cups.
Fill each mold halfway with juice.
Freeze for 1 hour or until frozen.
Arrange fruit slices on top of frozen juice, then slowly fill to top with juice.
Freeze.

title: lemon pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13 pan.
Hot out from oven, immediately spread crushed pineapple, including juice, over hot cake; cool at room temperature.
Mix milk with pudding and fold in Cool Whip; spread evenly over cake.
Best if made the day before and kept refrigerated.

title: egg dinner rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of flour and yeast; set aside.
In medium saucepan, heat: stir the milk, sugar, margarine or butter and salt just until warm (120° to 130°) and margarine almost melts.
Add to flour mixture, then add 3 egg yolks.
Beat with electric mixer on low to medium speed for 30 seconds, scraping the sides of the bowl.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in as much of remaining flour as you can.
On lightly floured surface, knead in enough of remaining flour to make moderately stiff dough.
Shape into a ball.
Place in a greased bowl; turn once.
Cover, let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough.
Turn onto lightly floured surface. Divide in half.
Then divide each half into 12 pieces.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash rice; add remaining ingredients and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in 275° oven for 3 hours.
Stir frequently during the first hour.
Add 1/2 cup raisins or 2 eggs during last hour.
Serves 6.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain pineapple slices, reserving juice; set juice aside. Layer fruit in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Combine pineapple juice, lemon juice, curry powder and cinnamon; pour mixture over layered fruit.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Yield:
6 servings (about 60 calories per serving).

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs and sugar until mixture is very stiff.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop cookie mixture onto lightly buttered tins in small spoonfuls and place in oven. Immediately turn oven off.
Let cookies remain in oven overnight.

title: hawaiian roast
directions: Brown
roast in 12-inch Dutch oven in oil.
Remove meat and brown vegetables.
Return meat to Dutch oven.
Add pineapple juice,
ginger, salt, pepper, sugar and soy sauce.	Cover Dutch oven
and
simmer for 2 1/2 hours.	Add pineapple chunks and cook 20 minutes more.
Transfer meat, vegetables and fruit to separate dish.
Mix water with the flour and stir into the juice
in
the Dutch
oven.
Simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.	Pour sauce over meat and vegetables.

title: finger jello
directions: Combine gelatins; add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Pour into large shallow pan (13 x 9-inch) and chill until firm. Cut into small squares and serve.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar well; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes (use two round cake pans).

title: cherry pie cake
directions: Pour pie filling into greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle cake mix over the cherries.
Melt oleo and pour over entire mixture. Top cake with chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: lisa's hawaiian kabobs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in saucepan; boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Pour mixture into a shallow dish.
Add chicken.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover and marinate at least 1 hour in refrigerator.
Stir mixture occasionally.

title: david's snack mix
directions: Sit on kitchen countertop (with parent standing by to assist!).
Use a one cup measure and a big bowl (or 5 gallon pail).
Measure ingredients in equal or other desirable ratios. Mix gently with wooden spoons.
Serve at snack time.

title: creamy potato soup(makes 9 cups)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water, covered, for 15 minutes, or until tender; drain.
Saute onion in margarine in a Dutch oven until tender.
Stir in the next 5 ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until hot.
Remove from heat.
Stir leftover mashed potatoes and diced potatoes and serve.
Garnish as desired.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Remove cloves and add remaining ingredients.
Heat to serve.
Makes 24 cups or 6 quarts.

title: katie's favorite bars(seven layer bars)
directions: Into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, put butter or margarine (melted) and add rest of ingredients in order, one on top of the other with condensed milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until slightly browned on top.
Allow to cool for a few minutes before cutting.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump ingredients into the pan in the following order: cherry pie filling, undrained pineapple, dry cake mix and pecans.
Smooth ingredients after each layer.
Do not mix.
Place the butter pieces on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serve with ice cream.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend lemon juice and condensed milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Use 1 package of graham crackers, crushed.
Add melted margarine and mix.
Shape graham cracker mixture into a pie dish with the back of your spoon.
Pour in lemon mixture and chill.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.

title: fudgy banana muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the flours, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl, combine bananas, milk, egg, oil and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups one-third full.
Break each candy bar into 12 pieces.
Place two pieces in each muffin cup.
Top with remaining batter.
Chop remaining candy bar pieces.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: baked beans #2
directions: Mix together gently.
Bake at 300°, uncovered.
Cover last hour.

title: montie's pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown chops and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Mix soup, milk, potatoes, salt, pepper, 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 can of the onion rings.
Spoon in greased 9 x 13-inch dish and arrange chops over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake uncovered 5 or 10 minutes more.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chocolate chips, margarine and corn syrup in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until melted and smooth. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla extract and sugar.
Add the Rice Krispies cereal, mixing lightly until well coated.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Store in the refrigerator.
Makes 48 squares.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Take 1 pint of canned tomato juice.
Put in onions, then put on stove and boil 10 minutes, then add a pinch of soda, dissolved in a little hot water.
Put in another kettle 1 pint of sweet milk.
As soon as it boils, remove from heat and add tomatoes. Add a hunk of butter and salt and pepper to taste.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Generously grease bottom and sides of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch). Mix all ingredients in pan with a fork; beat vigorously 1 minute. Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 55 to 65 minutes. Cool 5 to 10 minutes. Run knife around sides of loaf; remove from pan. If the loaf sticks, press gently on sides with the knife.
Serves 8. I don't know if you can freeze. Must do ahead.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Heat butter, Coke and cocoa; bring to a boil.
Pour over flour-sugar mixture.
Add other ingredients. Mix and pour into greased 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Crumble 4 soda crackers in pint baking dish.
Add cheese and crumble 4 more crackers.
Top with butter. Mix milk, eggs, salt, pepper and sugar.
Pour over the ingredients and bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes or until firm.
Serves two.

title: chocolate chip or butterscotch chip cookies
directions: Bake on greased sheet in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix package of Jell-O with 1 cup hot water; cut in cream cheese with beater and add lemon juice.
Add 1 cup of drained juice from can of fruit for salad.
Add whipped cream and mayonnaise and pinch of salt.
Add drained fruit and small can of crushed pineapple.

title: delicious cherry salad
directions: Mix all together.
Will keep in refrigerator up to 2 weeks. Freezes well.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels to make 2 cups; add 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press in dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Beat 1 cup sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour on top of pretzels. Mix boiling water and Jell-O; add strawberries.
Let this stand for 10 minutes.
Pour on top and chill.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Cream butter; add sugar and cream well. Add vanilla, flour and nuts. Drop on cookie sheet. Roll in powdered sugar while hot. Then roll again when cool. Makes 30 to 36.

title: easy drop biscuits
directions: Pre-heat oven to 400 degrees.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in the middle of the mixture.
Combine low fat yogurt, egg substitute, and vegetable oil; add yogurt mixture to flour mixture; stir until moist.
Drop the dough by rounded tablespoons about 2 inches apart onto a baking sheet coated with cooking spray, and bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
1 doz. Serving size:
1 biscuit.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Beat eggs, add milk.
Add dry ingredients to egg and milk.
Add oil. Bake in a greased iron skillet or muffin tin for about 20 minutes at 425°.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix milk and egg yolks in heavy pan; add dry ingredients.
Cook on medium to high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Let pudding cool, then pour into crust. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix in all remaining ingredients except noodles.
Mix in noodles and pour into a greased 7 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook for 3 hours.
Take meat out; add 3 cups water and 3 green peppers, sliced.
Slice meat thin; add to juices and peppers and cook for 30 minutes more.
Serve on French bread or beef buns.
(I serve this as a main meal dish and use leftovers for sandwiches.)

title: cucumber bread snack
directions: Mix cheese, dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread on slices of rye bread.
Put a slice of cucumber on each and sprinkle with dill weed.

title: bacon breakfast cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Add bacon bits, margarine and eggs.
Mix until well blended.
Add cereal and blend.
Drop by tablespoons 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: breakfast rice
directions: Cook Minute rice according to directions. Fry bacon and drain. Scramble eggs. Chop green onions. In large bowl, combine all these ingredients after cooking. Season with soy sauce to taste.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine. Follow with chocolate and butterscotch chips. Spread coconut evenly over chips. Pour milk over coconut. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before turning out of pan.
Cut in 1-inch squares. Makes about 10 dozen.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar and salt. Fold in vanilla and pecans or chocolate chips or both. Drop by teaspoon onto foil lined oven rack.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Place rack in oven and turn oven off!
Allow cookies to completely cool in oven before removing.

title: cranberry delight!
directions: Prepare Jell-O as per package directions.
Stir in Cool Whip until well blended.
Tear up angel food cake into small pieces and add to mixture.
Add strawberries.
Chill until Jell-O sets.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix ingredients together in saucepan.
Add cold water gradually, about 1/4 cup at a time, until you have added 1 1/2 to 2 cups.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it's the consistency of gravy.
Serve with hot buttered biscuits.

title: vegetable noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
In a bowl, combine soups, milk, 3/4 c. Parmesan, garlic, parsley, pepper and salt;
mix well.
Add noodles and vegetables; mix well.
Pour into greased 9X13 baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 c. Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes or until heated through. Serves 12-14.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and sour milk.
Blend milk.
Add dry ingredients, beating vigorously.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers in 1-inch slices.
Dissolve 2 cups slack lime in 2 quarts water and add 2 gallons more water.
Put pickles in mixture and let stand 24 hours.
Rinse several times in cold water and let stand 3 hours in cold ice water.
Drain well and put into mixture.
Bring to a boil sugar, salt, celery seed, vinegar, whole clove and pickling spice and boil 35 minutes or until clear.
Put in clear, sterilized jars and seal.
You may use your larger cucumbers if not bitter.

title: sugar pressed cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring thoroughly.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt together; blend in.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with 3-inch cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until cookies are a delicate golden color.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: peas and rice
directions: Wash peas, drain and place in pot with 2-quarts of water. Prepare coconut milk.
Put 1/2 pint coconut milk in boil for about 1 1/2 hours or until peas start breaking.
Add remainder of milk, thyme and salt to taste.
Wash rice, drain and add to peas.
Cook under slow fire until done.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine all ingredients; spread on crackers.
Yield:
1 2/3 cups.

title: parmesan bread deluxe
directions: In a small bowl, combine cheese, Marie's dressing and onion. Slice Italian bread into 1/2-inch slices.
Spread a generous teaspoon of the dressing mixture onto each slice.
Arrange bread, spread side up on cookie sheet.
Broil 2-inches from heat for 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: shrimp etouffee recipe
directions: Season shrimp with spices and set aside.
Melt oleo; add onions, celery, pepper and garlic.
Cook slowly until onions are wilted.
Add shrimp; simmer and stir occasionally.
Cook 20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add to mixture.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: oreo pie
directions: Put milk into bowl.
Dip Oreos in milk.
Line in dish and cover with Cool Whip.
Keep repeating this step until cookies are all used.
Best when refrigerated for about 1 hour before serving.

title: stuffed french toast for a crowd
directions: Beat eggs with milk and maple syrup.
Put 1/2 of the cubed bread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan, top with 1/2 cubed cream cheese; repeat with remaining.
Pour milk, eggs, syrup and mix over all.
Cover, refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake uncovered 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve with additional syrup.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach overnight in the refrigerator.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Serve with round corn chips.

title: fruity carrot salad
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise and juices. Fold the whipped cream into mayonnaise mixture. Pour over carrot mixture and toss to coat. Serve immediately. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: swedish oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Cream
margarine, sugar;
add
eggs,
one
at
a
time, beating after each
addition.
Add
vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately
with
sour cream, mixing well.
Save about 1/2 cup of batter for topping.
Spread rest of batter on greased jelly roll pan.
Spread can of cherry pie filling over batter and drop the
cup
of
saved batter by teaspoonful anywhere on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked pork chops and dressing
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides; add salt and pepper.
Place in sprayed pan.
Mix remaining ingredients except soup and 1/3 cup water.
Place mound of dressing on each chop.
Mix soup with 1/3 cup water.
Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine veggies, soup, cheese, sour cream, and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into greased one quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake uncovered for an additional 3 to 5 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: In large bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice; add cabbage, carrot and apple.
Mix well.
Cover and chill for several hours.

title: "idiot's delight" or dump cake
directions: Add ingredients in order to a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Slice very thin the stick of butter over the top of ingredients.
This is last item.
Bake 1 hour, more or less, at 350°.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Bake turkeys until done.
Remove from oven and shred all meat when cooled a little.
Return meat to roasting pan.
Chop onions, cover with water and boil until tender.
Pour onions and water over turkey.
Add Montgomery Inn/Ribs King barbecue sauce and Kraft barbecue sauce with honey.
Rinse bottles and add this water also to the turkey.
Mix well and return uncovered roasting pan to oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
This barbecue will be moist and delicious.
Can be made ahead of time and will be better warmed over.
Recipe can be halved.

title: fluffy frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold topping into mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm and serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Mix in order listed.
Let stand in refrigerator to chill.
Take out in small amounts.
Use as drop cookies.
Frost with vanilla frosting.

title: klondike sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Fold in sugar and flour.
Beat egg yolks.
Add salt and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Fold into egg whites. Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour before removing. Yields 16 servings.

title: fried pie crust
